79static isc_result_t
80check_orderent(const cfg_obj_t *ent, isc_log_t *logctx) {
81 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
82 isc_result_t tresult;
83 isc_textregion_t r;
84 dns_fixedname_t fixed;
85 const cfg_obj_t *obj;
86 dns_rdataclass_t rdclass;
87 dns_rdatatype_t rdtype;
88 isc_buffer_t b;
89 const char *str;
90
91 dns_fixedname_init(&fixed);
92 obj = cfg_tuple_get(ent, "class");
93 if (cfg_obj_isstring(obj)) {
94
95 DE_CONST(cfg_obj_asstring(obj), r.base);
96 r.length = strlen(r.base);
97 tresult = dns_rdataclass_fromtext(&rdclass, &r);
98 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
99 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
100 "rrset-order: invalid class '%s'",
101 r.base);
102 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
103 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
104 }
105 }
106
107 obj = cfg_tuple_get(ent, "type");
108 if (cfg_obj_isstring(obj)) {
109 DE_CONST(cfg_obj_asstring(obj), r.base);
110 r.length = strlen(r.base);
111 tresult = dns_rdatatype_fromtext(&rdtype, &r);
112 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
113 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
114 "rrset-order: invalid type '%s'",
115 r.base);
116 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
117 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
118 }
119 }
120
121 obj = cfg_tuple_get(ent, "name");
122 if (cfg_obj_isstring(obj)) {
123 str = cfg_obj_asstring(obj);
124 isc_buffer_constinit(&b, str, strlen(str));
125 isc_buffer_add(&b, strlen(str));
126 tresult = dns_name_fromtext(dns_fixedname_name(&fixed), &b,
127 dns_rootname, 0, NULL);
128 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
129 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
130 "rrset-order: invalid name '%s'", str);
131 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
132 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
133 }
134 }
135
136 obj = cfg_tuple_get(ent, "order");
137 if (!cfg_obj_isstring(obj) ||
138 strcasecmp("order", cfg_obj_asstring(obj)) != 0) {
139 cfg_obj_log(ent, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
140 "rrset-order: keyword 'order' missing");
141 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
142 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
143 }
144
145 obj = cfg_tuple_get(ent, "ordering");
146 if (!cfg_obj_isstring(obj)) {
147 cfg_obj_log(ent, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
148 "rrset-order: missing ordering");
149 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
150 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
151 } else if (strcasecmp(cfg_obj_asstring(obj), "fixed") == 0) {
152#if !DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
153 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
154 "rrset-order: order 'fixed' was disabled at "
155 "compilation time");
156#endif
157 } else if (strcasecmp(cfg_obj_asstring(obj), "random") != 0 &&
158 strcasecmp(cfg_obj_asstring(obj), "cyclic") != 0 &&
159 strcasecmp(cfg_obj_asstring(obj), "none") != 0) {
160 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
161 "rrset-order: invalid order '%s'",
162 cfg_obj_asstring(obj));
163 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
164 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
165 }
166 return (result);
167}

169static isc_result_t
170check_order(const cfg_obj_t *options, isc_log_t *logctx) {
171 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
172 isc_result_t tresult;
173 const cfg_listelt_t *element;
174 const cfg_obj_t *obj = NULL;
175
176 if (cfg_map_get(options, "rrset-order", &obj) != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
177 return (result);
178
179 for (element = cfg_list_first(obj);
180 element != NULL;
181 element = cfg_list_next(element))
182 {
183 tresult = check_orderent(cfg_listelt_value(element), logctx);
184 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS && tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
185 result = tresult;
186 }
187 return (result);
188}

190static isc_result_t
191check_dual_stack(const cfg_obj_t *options, isc_log_t *logctx) {
192 const cfg_listelt_t *element;
193 const cfg_obj_t *alternates = NULL;
194 const cfg_obj_t *value;
195 const cfg_obj_t *obj;
196 const char *str;
197 dns_fixedname_t fixed;
198 dns_name_t *name;
199 isc_buffer_t buffer;
200 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
201 isc_result_t tresult;
202
203 (void)cfg_map_get(options, "dual-stack-servers", &alternates);
204
205 if (alternates == NULL)
206 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
207
208 obj = cfg_tuple_get(alternates, "port");
209 if (cfg_obj_isuint32(obj)) {
210 uint32_t val = cfg_obj_asuint32(obj);
211 if (val > UINT16_MAX) {
212 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
213 "port '%u' out of range", val);
214 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
215 result = ISC_R_RANGE;
216 }
217 }
218 obj = cfg_tuple_get(alternates, "addresses");
219 for (element = cfg_list_first(obj);
220 element != NULL;
221 element = cfg_list_next(element)) {
222 value = cfg_listelt_value(element);
223 if (cfg_obj_issockaddr(value))
224 continue;
225 obj = cfg_tuple_get(value, "name");
226 str = cfg_obj_asstring(obj);
227 isc_buffer_constinit(&buffer, str, strlen(str));
228 isc_buffer_add(&buffer, strlen(str));
229 name = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixed);
230 tresult = dns_name_fromtext(name, &buffer, dns_rootname,
231 0, NULL);
232 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
233 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
234 "bad name '%s'", str);
235 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
236 result = tresult;
237 }
238 obj = cfg_tuple_get(value, "port");
239 if (cfg_obj_isuint32(obj)) {
240 uint32_t val = cfg_obj_asuint32(obj);
241 if (val > UINT16_MAX) {
242 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
243 "port '%u' out of range", val);
244 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
245 result = ISC_R_RANGE;
246 }
247 }
248 }
249 return (result);
250}

252static isc_result_t
253check_forward(const cfg_obj_t *options, const cfg_obj_t *global,
254 isc_log_t *logctx)
255{
256 const cfg_obj_t *forward = NULL;
257 const cfg_obj_t *forwarders = NULL;
258
259 (void)cfg_map_get(options, "forward", &forward);
260 (void)cfg_map_get(options, "forwarders", &forwarders);
261
262 if (forwarders != NULL && global != NULL) {
263 const char *file = cfg_obj_file(global);
264 unsigned int line = cfg_obj_line(global);
265 cfg_obj_log(forwarders, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
266 "forwarders declared in root zone and "
267 "in general configuration: %s:%u",
268 file, line);
269 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
270 }
271 if (forward != NULL && forwarders == NULL) {
272 cfg_obj_log(forward, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
273 "no matching 'forwarders' statement");
274 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
275 }
276 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
277}

279static isc_result_t
280disabled_algorithms(const cfg_obj_t *disabled, isc_log_t *logctx) {
281 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
282 isc_result_t tresult;
283 const cfg_listelt_t *element;
284 const char *str;
285 isc_buffer_t b;
286 dns_fixedname_t fixed;
287 dns_name_t *name;
288 const cfg_obj_t *obj;
289
290 name = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixed);
291 obj = cfg_tuple_get(disabled, "name");
292 str = cfg_obj_asstring(obj);
293 isc_buffer_constinit(&b, str, strlen(str));
294 isc_buffer_add(&b, strlen(str));
295 tresult = dns_name_fromtext(name, &b, dns_rootname, 0, NULL);
296 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
297 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
298 "bad domain name '%s'", str);
299 result = tresult;
300 }
301
302 obj = cfg_tuple_get(disabled, "algorithms");
303
304 for (element = cfg_list_first(obj);
305 element != NULL;
306 element = cfg_list_next(element))
307 {
308 isc_textregion_t r;
309 dns_secalg_t alg;
310
311 DE_CONST(cfg_obj_asstring(cfg_listelt_value(element)), r.base);
312 r.length = strlen(r.base);
313
314 tresult = dns_secalg_fromtext(&alg, &r);
315 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
316 cfg_obj_log(cfg_listelt_value(element), logctx,
317 ISC_LOG_ERROR, "invalid algorithm '%s'",
318 r.base);
319 result = tresult;
320 }
321 }
322 return (result);
323}

325static isc_result_t
326disabled_ds_digests(const cfg_obj_t *disabled, isc_log_t *logctx) {
327 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
328 isc_result_t tresult;
329 const cfg_listelt_t *element;
330 const char *str;
331 isc_buffer_t b;
332 dns_fixedname_t fixed;
333 dns_name_t *name;
334 const cfg_obj_t *obj;
335
336 name = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixed);
337 obj = cfg_tuple_get(disabled, "name");
338 str = cfg_obj_asstring(obj);
339 isc_buffer_constinit(&b, str, strlen(str));
340 isc_buffer_add(&b, strlen(str));
341 tresult = dns_name_fromtext(name, &b, dns_rootname, 0, NULL);
342 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
343 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
344 "bad domain name '%s'", str);
345 result = tresult;
346 }
347
348 obj = cfg_tuple_get(disabled, "digests");
349
350 for (element = cfg_list_first(obj);
351 element != NULL;
352 element = cfg_list_next(element))
353 {
354 isc_textregion_t r;
355 dns_dsdigest_t digest;
356
357 DE_CONST(cfg_obj_asstring(cfg_listelt_value(element)), r.base);
358 r.length = strlen(r.base);
359
360 /* works with a numeric argument too */
361 tresult = dns_dsdigest_fromtext(&digest, &r);
362 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
363 cfg_obj_log(cfg_listelt_value(element), logctx,
364 ISC_LOG_ERROR, "invalid digest type '%s'",
365 r.base);
366 result = tresult;
367 }
368 }
369 return (result);
370}

372static isc_result_t
373nameexist(const cfg_obj_t *obj, const char *name, int value,
374 isc_symtab_t *symtab, const char *fmt, isc_log_t *logctx,
375 isc_mem_t *mctx)
376{
377 char *key;
378 const char *file;
379 unsigned int line;
380 isc_result_t result;
381 isc_symvalue_t symvalue;
382
383 key = isc_mem_strdup(mctx, name);
384 if (key == NULL)
385 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
386 symvalue.as_cpointer = obj;
387 result = isc_symtab_define(symtab, key, value, symvalue,
388 isc_symexists_reject);
389 if (result == ISC_R_EXISTS) {
390 RUNTIME_CHECK(isc_symtab_lookup(symtab, key, value,
391 &symvalue) == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
392 file = cfg_obj_file(symvalue.as_cpointer);
393 line = cfg_obj_line(symvalue.as_cpointer);
394
395 if (file == NULL)
396 file = "<unknown file>";
397 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR, fmt, key, file, line);
398 isc_mem_free(mctx, key);
399 result = ISC_R_EXISTS;
400 } else if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
401 isc_mem_free(mctx, key);
402 }
403 return (result);
404}

406static isc_result_t
407mustbesecure(const cfg_obj_t *secure, isc_symtab_t *symtab, isc_log_t *logctx,
408 isc_mem_t *mctx)
409{
410 const cfg_obj_t *obj;
411 char namebuf[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
412 const char *str;
413 dns_fixedname_t fixed;
414 dns_name_t *name;
415 isc_buffer_t b;
416 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
417
418 name = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixed);
419 obj = cfg_tuple_get(secure, "name");
420 str = cfg_obj_asstring(obj);
421 isc_buffer_constinit(&b, str, strlen(str));
422 isc_buffer_add(&b, strlen(str));
423 result = dns_name_fromtext(name, &b, dns_rootname, 0, NULL);
424 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
425 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
426 "bad domain name '%s'", str);
427 } else {
428 dns_name_format(name, namebuf, sizeof(namebuf));
429 result = nameexist(secure, namebuf, 1, symtab,
430 "dnssec-must-be-secure '%s': already "
431 "exists previous definition: %s:%u",
432 logctx, mctx);
433 }
434 return (result);
435}

437static isc_result_t
438checkacl(const char *aclname, cfg_aclconfctx_t *actx, const cfg_obj_t *zconfig,
439 const cfg_obj_t *voptions, const cfg_obj_t *config,
440 isc_log_t *logctx, isc_mem_t *mctx)
441{
442 isc_result_t result;
443 const cfg_obj_t *aclobj = NULL;
444 const cfg_obj_t *options;
445 dns_acl_t *acl = NULL;
446
447 if (zconfig != NULL) {
448 options = cfg_tuple_get(zconfig, "options");
449 cfg_map_get(options, aclname, &aclobj);
450 }
451 if (voptions != NULL && aclobj == NULL)
452 cfg_map_get(voptions, aclname, &aclobj);
453 if (config != NULL && aclobj == NULL) {
454 options = NULL;
455 cfg_map_get(config, "options", &options);
456 if (options != NULL)
457 cfg_map_get(options, aclname, &aclobj);
458 }
459 if (aclobj == NULL)
460 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
461 result = cfg_acl_fromconfig(aclobj, config, logctx,
462 actx, mctx, 0, &acl);
463 if (acl != NULL)
464 dns_acl_detach(&acl);
465 return (result);
466}

468static isc_result_t
469check_viewacls(cfg_aclconfctx_t *actx, const cfg_obj_t *voptions,
470 const cfg_obj_t *config, isc_log_t *logctx, isc_mem_t *mctx)
471{
472 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS, tresult;
473 int i = 0;
474
475 static const char *acls[] = { "allow-query", "allow-query-on",
476 "allow-query-cache", "allow-query-cache-on",
477 "blackhole", "keep-response-order", "match-clients",
478 "match-destinations", "sortlist", NULL };
479
480 while (acls[i] != NULL) {
481 tresult = checkacl(acls[i++], actx, NULL, voptions, config,
482 logctx, mctx);
483 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
484 result = tresult;
485 }
486 return (result);
487}

489static const unsigned char zeros[16];
490
491static isc_result_t
492check_dns64(cfg_aclconfctx_t *actx, const cfg_obj_t *voptions,
493 const cfg_obj_t *config, isc_log_t *logctx, isc_mem_t *mctx)
494{
495 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
496 const cfg_obj_t *dns64 = NULL;
497 const cfg_obj_t *options;
498 const cfg_listelt_t *element;
499 const cfg_obj_t *map, *obj;
500 isc_netaddr_t na, sa;
501 unsigned int prefixlen;
502 int nbytes;
503 int i;
504
505 static const char *acls[] = { "clients", "exclude", "mapped", NULL};
506
507 if (voptions != NULL)
508 cfg_map_get(voptions, "dns64", &dns64);
509 if (config != NULL && dns64 == NULL) {
510 options = NULL;
511 cfg_map_get(config, "options", &options);
512 if (options != NULL)
513 cfg_map_get(options, "dns64", &dns64);
514 }
515 if (dns64 == NULL)
516 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
517
518 for (element = cfg_list_first(dns64);
519 element != NULL;
520 element = cfg_list_next(element))
521 {
522 map = cfg_listelt_value(element);
523 obj = cfg_map_getname(map);
524
525 cfg_obj_asnetprefix(obj, &na, &prefixlen);
526 if (na.family != AF_INET6) {
527 cfg_obj_log(map, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
528 "dns64 requires a IPv6 prefix");
529 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
530 continue;
531 }
532
533 if (prefixlen != 32 && prefixlen != 40 && prefixlen != 48 &&
534 prefixlen != 56 && prefixlen != 64 && prefixlen != 96) {
535 cfg_obj_log(map, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
536 "bad prefix length %u [32/40/48/56/64/96]",
537 prefixlen);
538 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
539 continue;
540 }
541
542 for (i = 0; acls[i] != NULL; i++) {
543 obj = NULL;
544 (void)cfg_map_get(map, acls[i], &obj);
545 if (obj != NULL) {
546 dns_acl_t *acl = NULL;
547 isc_result_t tresult;
548
549 tresult = cfg_acl_fromconfig(obj, config,
550 logctx, actx,
551 mctx, 0, &acl);
552 if (acl != NULL)
553 dns_acl_detach(&acl);
554 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
555 result = tresult;
556 }
557 }
558
559 obj = NULL;
560 (void)cfg_map_get(map, "suffix", &obj);
561 if (obj != NULL) {
562 isc_netaddr_fromsockaddr(&sa, cfg_obj_assockaddr(obj));
563 if (sa.family != AF_INET6) {
564 cfg_obj_log(map, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
565 "dns64 requires a IPv6 suffix");
566 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
567 continue;
568 }
569 nbytes = prefixlen / 8 + 4;
570 if (prefixlen <= 64)
571 nbytes++;
572 if (memcmp(sa.type.in6.s6_addr, zeros, nbytes) != 0) {
573 char netaddrbuf[ISC_NETADDR_FORMATSIZE];
574 isc_netaddr_format(&sa, netaddrbuf,
575 sizeof(netaddrbuf));
576 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
577 "bad suffix '%s' leading "
578 "%u octets not zeros",
579 netaddrbuf, nbytes);
580 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
581 }
582 }
583 }
584
585 return (result);
586}

588#define CHECK_RRL(cond, pat, val1, val2) \
589 do { \
590 if (!(cond)) { \
591 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR, \
592 pat, val1, val2); \
593 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) \
594 result = ISC_R_RANGE; \
595 } \
596 } while (0)
597
598#define CHECK_RRL_RATE(rate, def, max_rate, name) \
599 do { \
600 obj = NULL; \
601 mresult = cfg_map_get(map, name, &obj); \
602 if (mresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS) { \
603 rate = cfg_obj_asuint32(obj); \
604 CHECK_RRL(rate <= max_rate, name" %d > %d", \
605 rate, max_rate); \
606 } \
607 } while (0)

609static isc_result_t
610check_ratelimit(cfg_aclconfctx_t *actx, const cfg_obj_t *voptions,
611 const cfg_obj_t *config, isc_log_t *logctx, isc_mem_t *mctx)
612{
613 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
614 isc_result_t mresult;
615 const cfg_obj_t *map = NULL;
616 const cfg_obj_t *options;
617 const cfg_obj_t *obj;
618 int min_entries, i;
619 int all_per_second;
620 int errors_per_second;
621 int nodata_per_second;
622 int nxdomains_per_second;
623 int referrals_per_second;
624 int responses_per_second;
625 int slip;
626
627 if (voptions != NULL)
628 cfg_map_get(voptions, "rate-limit", &map);
629 if (config != NULL && map == NULL) {
630 options = NULL;
631 cfg_map_get(config, "options", &options);
632 if (options != NULL)
633 cfg_map_get(options, "rate-limit", &map);
634 }
635 if (map == NULL)
636 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
637
638 min_entries = 500;
639 obj = NULL;
640 mresult = cfg_map_get(map, "min-table-size", &obj);
641 if (mresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
642 min_entries = cfg_obj_asuint32(obj);
643 if (min_entries < 1)
644 min_entries = 1;
645 }
646
647 obj = NULL;
648 mresult = cfg_map_get(map, "max-table-size", &obj);
649 if (mresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
650 i = cfg_obj_asuint32(obj);
651 CHECK_RRL(i >= min_entries,
652 "max-table-size %d < min-table-size %d",
653 i, min_entries);
654 }
655
656 CHECK_RRL_RATE(responses_per_second, 0, DNS_RRL_MAX_RATE,
657 "responses-per-second");
658
659 CHECK_RRL_RATE(referrals_per_second, responses_per_second,
660 DNS_RRL_MAX_RATE, "referrals-per-second");
661 CHECK_RRL_RATE(nodata_per_second, responses_per_second,
662 DNS_RRL_MAX_RATE, "nodata-per-second");
663 CHECK_RRL_RATE(nxdomains_per_second, responses_per_second,
664 DNS_RRL_MAX_RATE, "nxdomains-per-second");
665 CHECK_RRL_RATE(errors_per_second, responses_per_second,
666 DNS_RRL_MAX_RATE, "errors-per-second");
667
668 CHECK_RRL_RATE(all_per_second, 0, DNS_RRL_MAX_RATE, "all-per-second");
669
670 CHECK_RRL_RATE(slip, 2, DNS_RRL_MAX_SLIP, "slip");
671
672 obj = NULL;
673 mresult = cfg_map_get(map, "window", &obj);
674 if (mresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
675 i = cfg_obj_asuint32(obj);
676 CHECK_RRL(i >= 1 && i <= DNS_RRL_MAX_WINDOW,
677 "window %d < 1 or > %d", i, DNS_RRL_MAX_WINDOW);
678 }
679
680 obj = NULL;
681 mresult = cfg_map_get(map, "qps-scale", &obj);
682 if (mresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
683 i = cfg_obj_asuint32(obj);
684 CHECK_RRL(i >= 1, "invalid 'qps-scale %d'%s", i, "");
685 }
686
687 obj = NULL;
688 mresult = cfg_map_get(map, "ipv4-prefix-length", &obj);
689 if (mresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
690 i = cfg_obj_asuint32(obj);
691 CHECK_RRL(i >= 8 && i <= 32,
692 "invalid 'ipv4-prefix-length %d'%s", i, "");
693 }
694
695 obj = NULL;
696 mresult = cfg_map_get(map, "ipv6-prefix-length", &obj);
697 if (mresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
698 i = cfg_obj_asuint32(obj);
699 CHECK_RRL(i >= 16 && i <= DNS_RRL_MAX_PREFIX,
700 "ipv6-prefix-length %d < 16 or > %d",
701 i, DNS_RRL_MAX_PREFIX);
702 }
703
704 obj = NULL;
705 (void)cfg_map_get(map, "exempt-clients", &obj);
706 if (obj != NULL) {
707 dns_acl_t *acl = NULL;
708 isc_result_t tresult;
709
710 tresult = cfg_acl_fromconfig(obj, config, logctx, actx,
711 mctx, 0, &acl);
712 if (acl != NULL)
713 dns_acl_detach(&acl);
714 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
715 result = tresult;
716 }
717
718 return (result);
719}

721/*
722 * Check allow-recursion and allow-recursion-on acls, and also log a
723 * warning if they're inconsistent with the "recursion" option.
724 */
725static isc_result_t
726check_recursionacls(cfg_aclconfctx_t *actx, const cfg_obj_t *voptions,
727 const char *viewname, const cfg_obj_t *config,
728 isc_log_t *logctx, isc_mem_t *mctx)
729{
730 const cfg_obj_t *options, *aclobj, *obj = NULL;
731 dns_acl_t *acl = NULL;
732 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS, tresult;
733 bool recursion;
734 const char *forview = " for view ";
735 int i = 0;
736
737 static const char *acls[] = { "allow-recursion", "allow-recursion-on",
738 NULL };
739
740 if (voptions != NULL)
741 cfg_map_get(voptions, "recursion", &obj);
742 if (obj == NULL && config != NULL) {
743 options = NULL;
744 cfg_map_get(config, "options", &options);
745 if (options != NULL)
746 cfg_map_get(options, "recursion", &obj);
747 }
748 if (obj == NULL)
749 recursion = true;
750 else
751 recursion = cfg_obj_asboolean(obj);
752
753 if (viewname == NULL) {
754 viewname = "";
755 forview = "";
756 }
757
758 for (i = 0; acls[i] != NULL; i++) {
759 aclobj = options = NULL;
760 acl = NULL;
761
762 if (voptions != NULL)
763 cfg_map_get(voptions, acls[i], &aclobj);
764 if (config != NULL && aclobj == NULL) {
765 options = NULL;
766 cfg_map_get(config, "options", &options);
767 if (options != NULL)
768 cfg_map_get(options, acls[i], &aclobj);
769 }
770 if (aclobj == NULL)
771 continue;
772
773 tresult = cfg_acl_fromconfig(aclobj, config, logctx,
774 actx, mctx, 0, &acl);
775
776 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
777 result = tresult;
778
779 if (acl == NULL)
780 continue;
781
782 if (recursion == false && !dns_acl_isnone(acl)) {
783 cfg_obj_log(aclobj, logctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
784 "both \"recursion no;\" and "
785 "\"%s\" active%s%s",
786 acls[i], forview, viewname);
787 }
788
789 if (acl != NULL)
790 dns_acl_detach(&acl);
791 }
792
793 return (result);
794}

817static isc_result_t
818check_dscp(const cfg_obj_t *options, isc_log_t *logctx) {
819 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
820 const cfg_obj_t *obj = NULL;
821
822 /*
823 * Check that DSCP setting is within range
824 */
825 obj = NULL;
826 (void)cfg_map_get(options, "dscp", &obj);
827 if (obj != NULL) {
828 uint32_t dscp = cfg_obj_asuint32(obj);
829 if (dscp >= 64) {
830 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
831 "'dscp' out of range (0-63)");
832 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
833 }
834 }
835
836 return (result);
837}

839static isc_result_t
840check_name(const char *str) {
841 dns_fixedname_t fixed;
842
843 dns_fixedname_init(&fixed);
844 return (dns_name_fromstring(dns_fixedname_name(&fixed), str, 0, NULL));
845}
846
847static isc_result_t
848check_options(const cfg_obj_t *options, isc_log_t *logctx, isc_mem_t *mctx,
849 optlevel_t optlevel)
850{
851 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
852 isc_result_t tresult;
853 unsigned int i;
854 const cfg_obj_t *obj = NULL;
855 const cfg_obj_t *resignobj = NULL;
856 const cfg_listelt_t *element;
857 isc_symtab_t *symtab = NULL;
858 dns_fixedname_t fixed;
859 const char *str;
860 dns_name_t *name;
861 isc_buffer_t b;
862 uint32_t lifetime = 3600;
863 const char *ccalg = "aes";
864
865 /*
866 * { "name", scale, value }
867 * (scale * value) <= UINT32_MAX
868 */
869 static intervaltable intervals[] = {
870 { "cleaning-interval", 60, 28 * 24 * 60 }, /* 28 days */
871 { "heartbeat-interval", 60, 28 * 24 * 60 }, /* 28 days */
872 { "interface-interval", 60, 28 * 24 * 60 }, /* 28 days */
873 { "max-transfer-idle-in", 60, 28 * 24 * 60 }, /* 28 days */
874 { "max-transfer-idle-out", 60, 28 * 24 * 60 }, /* 28 days */
875 { "max-transfer-time-in", 60, 28 * 24 * 60 }, /* 28 days */
876 { "max-transfer-time-out", 60, 28 * 24 * 60 }, /* 28 days */
877 { "statistics-interval", 60, 28 * 24 * 60 }, /* 28 days */
878
879 /* minimum and maximum cache and negative cache TTLs */
880 { "min-cache-ttl", 1, MAX_MIN_CACHE_TTL }, /* 90 secs */
881 { "max-cache-ttl", 1, UINT32_MAX }, /* no limit */
882 { "min-ncache-ttl", 1, MAX_MIN_NCACHE_TTL}, /* 90 secs */
883 { "max-ncache-ttl", 1, MAX_MAX_NCACHE_TTL }, /* 7 days */
884 };
885
886 static const char *server_contact[] = {
887 "empty-server", "empty-contact",
888 "dns64-server", "dns64-contact",
889 NULL
890 };
891
892#ifdef HAVE_DNSTAP
893 static fstrmtable fstrm[] = {
894 {
895 "fstrm-set-buffer-hint",
896 FSTRM_IOTHR_BUFFER_HINT_MIN,
897 FSTRM_IOTHR_BUFFER_HINT_MAX
898 },
899 {
900 "fstrm-set-flush-timeout",
901 FSTRM_IOTHR_FLUSH_TIMEOUT_MIN,
902 FSTRM_IOTHR_FLUSH_TIMEOUT_MAX
903 },
904 {
905 "fstrm-set-input-queue-size",
906 FSTRM_IOTHR_INPUT_QUEUE_SIZE_MIN,
907 FSTRM_IOTHR_INPUT_QUEUE_SIZE_MAX
908 },
909 {
910 "fstrm-set-output-notify-threshold",
911 FSTRM_IOTHR_QUEUE_NOTIFY_THRESHOLD_MIN,
912 0
913 },
914 {
915 "fstrm-set-output-queue-size",
916 FSTRM_IOTHR_OUTPUT_QUEUE_SIZE_MIN,
917 FSTRM_IOTHR_OUTPUT_QUEUE_SIZE_MAX
918 },
919 {
920 "fstrm-set-reopen-interval",
921 FSTRM_IOTHR_REOPEN_INTERVAL_MIN,
922 FSTRM_IOTHR_REOPEN_INTERVAL_MAX
923 }
924 };
925#endif
926
927 /*
928 * Check that fields specified in units of time other than seconds
929 * have reasonable values.
930 */
931 for (i = 0; i < sizeof(intervals) / sizeof(intervals[0]); i++) {
932 uint32_t val;
933 obj = NULL;
934 (void)cfg_map_get(options, intervals[i].name, &obj);
935 if (obj == NULL)
936 continue;
937 val = cfg_obj_asuint32(obj);
938 if (val > intervals[i].max) {
939 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
940 "%s '%u' is out of range (0..%u)",
941 intervals[i].name, val,
942 intervals[i].max);
943 result = ISC_R_RANGE;
944 } else if (val > (UINT32_MAX / intervals[i].scale)) {
945 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
946 "%s '%d' is out of range",
947 intervals[i].name, val);
948 result = ISC_R_RANGE;
949 }
950 }
951
952 obj = NULL;
953 cfg_map_get(options, "max-rsa-exponent-size", &obj);
954 if (obj != NULL) {
955 uint32_t val;
956
957 val = cfg_obj_asuint32(obj);
958 if (val != 0 && (val < 35 || val > 4096)) {
959 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
960 "max-rsa-exponent-size '%u' is out of "
961 "range (35..4096)", val);
962 result = ISC_R_RANGE;
963 }
964 }
965
966 obj = NULL;
967 cfg_map_get(options, "sig-validity-interval", &obj);
968 if (obj != NULL) {
969 uint32_t validity, resign = 0;
970
971 validity = cfg_obj_asuint32(cfg_tuple_get(obj, "validity"));
972 resignobj = cfg_tuple_get(obj, "re-sign");
973 if (!cfg_obj_isvoid(resignobj))
974 resign = cfg_obj_asuint32(resignobj);
975
976 if (validity > 3660 || validity == 0) { /* 10 years */
977 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
978 "%s '%u' is out of range (1..3660)",
979 "sig-validity-interval", validity);
980 result = ISC_R_RANGE;
981 }
982
983 if (!cfg_obj_isvoid(resignobj)) {
984 if (resign > 3660 || resign == 0) { /* 10 years */
985 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
986 "%s '%u' is out of range (1..3660)",
987 "sig-validity-interval (re-sign)",
988 validity);
989 result = ISC_R_RANGE;
990 } else if ((validity > 7 && validity < resign) ||
991 (validity <= 7 && validity * 24 < resign)) {
992 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
993 "validity interval (%u days) "
994 "less than re-signing interval "
995 "(%u %s)", validity, resign,
996 (validity > 7) ? "days" : "hours");
997 result = ISC_R_RANGE;
998 }
999 }
1000 }
1001
1002 obj = NULL;
1003 cfg_map_get(options, "dnskey-sig-validity", &obj);
1004 if (obj != NULL) {
1005 uint32_t keyvalidity;
1006
1007 keyvalidity = cfg_obj_asuint32(obj);
1008 if (keyvalidity > 3660 || keyvalidity == 0) { /* 10 years */
1009 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1010 "%s '%u' is out of range (1..3660)",
1011 "dnskey-sig-validity",
1012 keyvalidity);
1013 result = ISC_R_RANGE;
1014 }
1015
1016 }
1017
1018 obj = NULL;
1019 (void)cfg_map_get(options, "preferred-glue", &obj);
1020 if (obj != NULL) {
1021 str = cfg_obj_asstring(obj);
1022 if (strcasecmp(str, "a") != 0 &&
1023 strcasecmp(str, "aaaa") != 0 &&
1024 strcasecmp(str, "none") != 0)
1025 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1026 "preferred-glue unexpected value '%s'",
1027 str);
1028 }
1029
1030 obj = NULL;
1031 (void)cfg_map_get(options, "root-delegation-only", &obj);
1032 if (obj != NULL) {
1033 if (!cfg_obj_isvoid(obj)) {
1034 for (element = cfg_list_first(obj);
1035 element != NULL;
1036 element = cfg_list_next(element)) {
1037 const cfg_obj_t *exclude;
1038
1039 exclude = cfg_listelt_value(element);
1040 str = cfg_obj_asstring(exclude);
1041 tresult = check_name(str);
1042 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1043 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1044 "bad domain name '%s'",
1045 str);
1046 result = tresult;
1047 }
1048 }
1049 }
1050 }
1051
1052 /*
1053 * Set supported DNSSEC algorithms.
1054 */
1055 obj = NULL;
1056 (void)cfg_map_get(options, "disable-algorithms", &obj);
1057 if (obj != NULL) {
1058 for (element = cfg_list_first(obj);
1059 element != NULL;
1060 element = cfg_list_next(element))
1061 {
1062 obj = cfg_listelt_value(element);
1063 tresult = disabled_algorithms(obj, logctx);
1064 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1065 result = tresult;
1066 }
1067 }
1068
1069 /*
1070 * Set supported DS/DLV digest types.
1071 */
1072 obj = NULL;
1073 (void)cfg_map_get(options, "disable-ds-digests", &obj);
1074 if (obj != NULL) {
1075 for (element = cfg_list_first(obj);
1076 element != NULL;
1077 element = cfg_list_next(element))
1078 {
1079 obj = cfg_listelt_value(element);
1080 tresult = disabled_ds_digests(obj, logctx);
1081 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1082 result = tresult;
1083 }
1084 }
1085
1086 name = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixed);
1087
1088 /*
1089 * Check the DLV zone name.
1090 */
1091 obj = NULL;
1092 (void)cfg_map_get(options, "dnssec-lookaside", &obj);
1093 if (obj != NULL) {
1094 tresult = isc_symtab_create(mctx, 100, freekey, mctx,
1095 false, &symtab);
1096 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1097 result = tresult;
1098 for (element = cfg_list_first(obj);
1099 element != NULL;
1100 element = cfg_list_next(element))
1101 {
1102 const char *dlv;
1103 const cfg_obj_t *dlvobj, *anchor;
1104
1105 obj = cfg_listelt_value(element);
1106
1107 anchor = cfg_tuple_get(obj, "trust-anchor");
1108 dlvobj = cfg_tuple_get(obj, "domain");
1109 dlv = cfg_obj_asstring(dlvobj);
1110
1111 /*
1112 * If domain is "auto" or "no" and trust anchor
1113 * is missing, skip remaining tests
1114 */
1115 if (cfg_obj_isvoid(anchor)) {
1116 if (!strcasecmp(dlv, "no")) {
1117 continue;
1118 }
1119 if (!strcasecmp(dlv, "auto")) {
1120 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
1121 "dnssec-lookaside 'auto' "
1122 "is no longer supported");
1123 continue;
1124 }
1125 }
1126
1127 tresult = dns_name_fromstring(name, dlv, 0, NULL);
1128 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1129 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1130 "bad domain name '%s'", dlv);
1131 result = tresult;
1132 continue;
1133 }
1134 if (symtab != NULL) {
1135 tresult = nameexist(obj, dlv, 1, symtab,
1136 "dnssec-lookaside '%s': "
1137 "already exists; previous "
1138 "definition: %s:%u",
1139 logctx, mctx);
1140 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS &&
1141 result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1142 result = tresult;
1143 }
1144
1145 /*
1146 * XXXMPA to be removed when multiple lookaside
1147 * namespaces are supported.
1148 */
1149 if (!dns_name_equal(dns_rootname, name)) {
1150 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1151 "dnssec-lookaside '%s': "
1152 "non-root not yet supported", dlv);
1153 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1154 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
1155 }
1156
1157 if (cfg_obj_isvoid(anchor)) {
1158 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1159 "dnssec-lookaside requires "
1160 "either or 'no' or a "
1161 "domain and trust anchor");
1162 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1163 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
1164 continue;
1165 }
1166
1167 dlv = cfg_obj_asstring(anchor);
1168 tresult = dns_name_fromstring(name, dlv, 0, NULL);
1169 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1170 cfg_obj_log(anchor, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1171 "bad domain name '%s'", dlv);
1172 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1173 result = tresult;
1174 continue;
1175 }
1176 if (dns_name_equal(&dlviscorg, name)) {
1177 cfg_obj_log(anchor, logctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
1178 "dlv.isc.org has been shut down");
1179 continue;
1180 }
1181 }
1182
1183 if (symtab != NULL)
1184 isc_symtab_destroy(&symtab);
1185 }
1186
1187 /*
1188 * Check auto-dnssec at the view/options level
1189 */
1190 obj = NULL;
1191 (void)cfg_map_get(options, "auto-dnssec", &obj);
1192 if (obj != NULL) {
1193 const char *arg = cfg_obj_asstring(obj);
1194 if (optlevel != optlevel_zone && strcasecmp(arg, "off") != 0) {
1195 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1196 "auto-dnssec may only be activated at the "
1197 "zone level");
1198 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1199 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
1200 }
1201 }
1202
1203 /*
1204 * Check dnssec-must-be-secure.
1205 */
1206 obj = NULL;
1207 (void)cfg_map_get(options, "dnssec-must-be-secure", &obj);
1208 if (obj != NULL) {
1209 tresult = isc_symtab_create(mctx, 100, freekey, mctx,
1210 false, &symtab);
1211 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1212 result = tresult;
1213 for (element = cfg_list_first(obj);
1214 element != NULL;
1215 element = cfg_list_next(element))
1216 {
1217 obj = cfg_listelt_value(element);
1218 tresult = mustbesecure(obj, symtab, logctx, mctx);
1219 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS && tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1220 result = tresult;
1221 }
1222 if (symtab != NULL)
1223 isc_symtab_destroy(&symtab);
1224 }
1225
1226 /*
1227 * Check server/contacts for syntactic validity.
1228 */
1229 for (i= 0; server_contact[i] != NULL; i++) {
1230 obj = NULL;
1231 (void)cfg_map_get(options, server_contact[i], &obj);
1232 if (obj != NULL) {
1233 str = cfg_obj_asstring(obj);
1234 if (check_name(str) != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1235 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1236 "%s: invalid name '%s'",
1237 server_contact[i], str);
1238 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1239 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
1240 }
1241 }
1242 }
1243
1244 /*
1245 * Check empty zone configuration.
1246 */
1247 obj = NULL;
1248 (void)cfg_map_get(options, "disable-empty-zone", &obj);
1249 for (element = cfg_list_first(obj);
1250 element != NULL;
1251 element = cfg_list_next(element))
1252 {
1253 obj = cfg_listelt_value(element);
1254 str = cfg_obj_asstring(obj);
1255 if (check_name(str) != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1256 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1257 "disable-empty-zone: invalid name '%s'",
1258 str);
1259 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1260 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
1261 }
1262 }
1263
1264 /*
1265 * Check that server-id is not too long.
1266 * 1024 bytes should be big enough.
1267 */
1268 obj = NULL;
1269 (void)cfg_map_get(options, "server-id", &obj);
1270 if (obj != NULL && cfg_obj_isstring(obj) &&
1271 strlen(cfg_obj_asstring(obj)) > 1024U) {
1272 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1273 "'server-id' too big (>1024 bytes)");
1274 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1275 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
1276 }
1277
1278 tresult = check_dscp(options, logctx);
1279 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS && tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1280 result = tresult;
1281
1282 obj = NULL;
1283 (void)cfg_map_get(options, "nta-lifetime", &obj);
1284 if (obj != NULL) {
1285 lifetime = cfg_obj_asuint32(obj);
1286 if (lifetime > 604800) { /* 7 days */
1287 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1288 "'nta-lifetime' cannot exceed one week");
1289 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1290 result = ISC_R_RANGE;
1291 } else if (lifetime == 0) {
1292 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1293 "'nta-lifetime' may not be zero");
1294 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1295 result = ISC_R_RANGE;
1296 }
1297 }
1298
1299 obj = NULL;
1300 (void)cfg_map_get(options, "nta-recheck", &obj);
1301 if (obj != NULL) {
1302 uint32_t recheck = cfg_obj_asuint32(obj);
1303 if (recheck > 604800) { /* 7 days */
1304 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1305 "'nta-recheck' cannot exceed one week");
1306 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1307 result = ISC_R_RANGE;
1308 }
1309
1310 if (recheck > lifetime)
1311 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
1312 "'nta-recheck' (%d seconds) is "
1313 "greater than 'nta-lifetime' "
1314 "(%d seconds)", recheck, lifetime);
1315 }
1316
1317 obj = NULL;
1318 (void) cfg_map_get(options, "cookie-algorithm", &obj);
1319 if (obj != NULL) {
1320 ccalg = cfg_obj_asstring(obj);
1321 }
1322
1323 obj = NULL;
1324 (void) cfg_map_get(options, "cookie-secret", &obj);
1325 if (obj != NULL) {
1326 unsigned char secret[32];
1327
1328 for (element = cfg_list_first(obj);
1329 element != NULL;
1330 element = cfg_list_next(element)) {
1331 unsigned int usedlength;
1332
1333 obj = cfg_listelt_value(element);
1334 str = cfg_obj_asstring(obj);
1335
1336 memset(secret, 0, sizeof(secret));
1337 isc_buffer_init(&b, secret, sizeof(secret));
1338 tresult = isc_hex_decodestring(str, &b);
1339 if (tresult == ISC_R_NOSPACE) {
1340 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1341 "cookie-secret: too long");
1342 } else if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1343 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1344 "cookie-secret: invalid hex "
1345 "string");
1346 }
1347 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1348 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1349 result = tresult;
1350 continue;
1351 }
1352
1353 usedlength = isc_buffer_usedlength(&b);
1354 if (strcasecmp(ccalg, "aes") == 0 &&
1355 usedlength != ISC_AES128_KEYLENGTH) {
1356 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1357 "AES cookie-secret must be "
1358 "128 bits");
1359 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1360 result = ISC_R_RANGE;
1361 }
1362 if (strcasecmp(ccalg, "sha1") == 0 &&
1363 usedlength != ISC_SHA1_DIGESTLENGTH) {
1364 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1365 "SHA1 cookie-secret must be "
1366 "160 bits");
1367 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1368 result = ISC_R_RANGE;
1369 }
1370 if (strcasecmp(ccalg, "sha256") == 0 &&
1371 usedlength != ISC_SHA256_DIGESTLENGTH) {
1372 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1373 "SHA256 cookie-secret must be "
1374 "256 bits");
1375 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1376 result = ISC_R_RANGE;
1377 }
1378 }
1379 }
1380
1381#ifdef HAVE_DNSTAP
1382 for (i = 0; i < sizeof(fstrm) / sizeof(fstrm[0]); i++) {
1383 uint32_t value;
1384
1385 obj = NULL;
1386 (void) cfg_map_get(options, fstrm[i].name, &obj);
1387 if (obj == NULL)
1388 continue;
1389
1390 value = cfg_obj_asuint32(obj);
1391 if (value < fstrm[i].min ||
1392 (fstrm[i].max != 0U && value > fstrm[i].max)) {
1393 if (fstrm[i].max != 0U)
1394 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1395 "%s '%u' out of range (%u..%u)",
1396 fstrm[i].name, value,
1397 fstrm[i].min, fstrm[i].max);
1398 else
1399 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1400 "%s out of range (%u < %u)",
1401 fstrm[i].name, value, fstrm[i].min);
1402 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1403 result = ISC_R_RANGE;
1404 }
1405
1406 if (strcmp(fstrm[i].name, "fstrm-set-input-queue-size") == 0) {
1407 int bits = 0;
1408 do {
1409 bits += value & 0x1;
1410 value >>= 1;
1411 } while (value != 0U);
1412 if (bits != 1) {
1413 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1414 "%s '%u' not a power-of-2",
1415 fstrm[i].name,
1416 cfg_obj_asuint32(obj));
1417 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1418 result = ISC_R_RANGE;
1419 }
1420 }
1421 }
1422
1423 /* Check that dnstap-ouput values are consistent */
1424 obj = NULL;
1425 (void) cfg_map_get(options, "dnstap-output", &obj);
1426 if (obj != NULL) {
1427 const cfg_obj_t *obj2;
1428 dns_dtmode_t dmode;
1429
1430 obj2 = cfg_tuple_get(obj, "mode");
1431 if (obj2 == NULL) {
1432 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1433 "dnstap-output mode not found");
1434 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1435 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
1436 } else {
1437 if (strcasecmp(cfg_obj_asstring(obj2), "file") == 0)
1438 dmode = dns_dtmode_file;
1439 else
1440 dmode = dns_dtmode_unix;
1441
1442 obj2 = cfg_tuple_get(obj, "size");
1443 if (obj2 != NULL && !cfg_obj_isvoid(obj2) &&
1444 dmode == dns_dtmode_unix)
1445 {
1446 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1447 "dnstap-output size "
1448 "cannot be set with mode unix");
1449 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1450 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
1451 }
1452
1453 obj2 = cfg_tuple_get(obj, "versions");
1454 if (obj2 != NULL && !cfg_obj_isvoid(obj2) &&
1455 dmode == dns_dtmode_unix)
1456 {
1457 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1458 "dnstap-output versions "
1459 "cannot be set with mode unix");
1460 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1461 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
1462 }
1463
1464 obj2 = cfg_tuple_get(obj, "suffix");
1465 if (obj2 != NULL && !cfg_obj_isvoid(obj2) &&
1466 dmode == dns_dtmode_unix)
1467 {
1468 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1469 "dnstap-output suffix "
1470 "cannot be set with mode unix");
1471 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1472 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
1473 }
1474 }
1475 }
1476#endif
1477
1478 obj = NULL;
1479 (void)cfg_map_get(options, "lmdb-mapsize", &obj);
1480 if (obj != NULL) {
1481 uint64_t mapsize = cfg_obj_asuint64(obj);
1482
1483 if (mapsize < (1ULL << 20)) { /* 1 megabyte */
1484 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx,
1485 ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1486 "'lmdb-mapsize "
1487 "%" PRId64 "' "
1488 "is too small",
1489 mapsize);
1490 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1491 result = ISC_R_RANGE;
1492 } else if (mapsize > (1ULL << 40)) { /* 1 terabyte */
1493 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx,
1494 ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1495 "'lmdb-mapsize "
1496 "%" PRId64 "' "
1497 "is too large",
1498 mapsize);
1499 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1500 result = ISC_R_RANGE;
1501 }
1502 }
1503
1504 obj = NULL;
1505 (void)cfg_map_get(options, "resolver-nonbackoff-tries", &obj);
1506 if (obj != NULL && cfg_obj_asuint32(obj) == 0U) {
1507 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1508 "'resolver-nonbackoff-tries' must be >= 1");
1509 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1510 result = ISC_R_RANGE;
1511 }
1512
1513 obj = NULL;
1514 (void)cfg_map_get(options, "geoip-use-ecs", &obj);
1515 if (obj != NULL && cfg_obj_asboolean(obj)) {
1516 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1517 "'geoip-use-ecs yes': "
1518 "ECS can no longer be used in geoip ACLs");
1519 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1520 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
1521 }
1522 }
1523
1524 return (result);
1525}

1528get_masters_def(const cfg_obj_t *cctx, const char *name, const cfg_obj_t **ret) {
1529 isc_result_t result;

1532

1553static isc_result_t
1554validate_masters(const cfg_obj_t *obj, const cfg_obj_t *config,
1555 uint32_t *countp, isc_log_t *logctx, isc_mem_t *mctx)
1556{
1557 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
1558 isc_result_t tresult;
1559 uint32_t count = 0;
1560 isc_symtab_t *symtab = NULL;
1561 isc_symvalue_t symvalue;
1562 const cfg_listelt_t *element;
1563 const cfg_listelt_t **stack = NULL;
1564 uint32_t stackcount = 0, pushed = 0;
1565 const cfg_obj_t *list;
1566
1567 REQUIRE(countp != NULL);
1568 result = isc_symtab_create(mctx, 100, NULL, NULL, false, &symtab);
1569 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1570 *countp = count;
1571 return (result);
1572 }
1573
1574 newlist:
1575 list = cfg_tuple_get(obj, "addresses");
1576 element = cfg_list_first(list);
1577 resume:
1578 for ( ;
1579 element != NULL;
1580 element = cfg_list_next(element))
1581 {
1582 const char *listname;
1583 const cfg_obj_t *addr;
1584 const cfg_obj_t *key;
1585
1586 addr = cfg_tuple_get(cfg_listelt_value(element),
1587 "masterselement");
1588 key = cfg_tuple_get(cfg_listelt_value(element), "key");
1589
1590 if (cfg_obj_issockaddr(addr)) {
1591 count++;
1592 continue;
1593 }
1594 if (!cfg_obj_isvoid(key)) {
1595 cfg_obj_log(key, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1596 "unexpected token '%s'",
1597 cfg_obj_asstring(key));
1598 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1599 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
1600 }
1601 listname = cfg_obj_asstring(addr);
1602 symvalue.as_cpointer = addr;
1603 tresult = isc_symtab_define(symtab, listname, 1, symvalue,
1604 isc_symexists_reject);
1605 if (tresult == ISC_R_EXISTS)
1606 continue;
1607 tresult = get_masters_def(config, listname, &obj);
1608 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1609 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1610 result = tresult;
1611 cfg_obj_log(addr, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1612 "unable to find masters list '%s'",
1613 listname);
1614 continue;
1615 }
1616 /* Grow stack? */
1617 if (stackcount == pushed) {
1618 void * newstack;
1619 uint32_t newlen = stackcount + 16;
1620 size_t newsize, oldsize;
1621
1622 newsize = newlen * sizeof(*stack);
1623 oldsize = stackcount * sizeof(*stack);
1624 newstack = isc_mem_get(mctx, newsize);
1625 if (newstack == NULL)
1626 goto cleanup;
1627 if (stackcount != 0) {
1628 void *ptr;
1629
1630 DE_CONST(stack, ptr);
1631 memmove(newstack, stack, oldsize);
1632 isc_mem_put(mctx, ptr, oldsize);
1633 }
1634 stack = newstack;
1635 stackcount = newlen;
1636 }
1637 stack[pushed++] = cfg_list_next(element);
1638 goto newlist;
1639 }
1640 if (pushed != 0) {
1641 element = stack[--pushed];
1642 goto resume;
1643 }
1644 cleanup:
1645 if (stack != NULL) {
1646 void *ptr;
1647
1648 DE_CONST(stack, ptr);
1649 isc_mem_put(mctx, ptr, stackcount * sizeof(*stack));
1650 }
1651 isc_symtab_destroy(&symtab);
1652 *countp = count;
1653 return (result);
1654}

1656static isc_result_t
1657check_update_policy(const cfg_obj_t *policy, isc_log_t *logctx) {
1658 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
1659 isc_result_t tresult;
1660 const cfg_listelt_t *element;
1661 const cfg_listelt_t *element2;
1662 dns_fixedname_t fixed_id, fixed_name;
1663 dns_name_t *id, *name;
1664 const char *str;
1665 isc_textregion_t r;
1666 dns_rdatatype_t type;
1667
1668 /* Check for "update-policy local;" */
1669 if (cfg_obj_isstring(policy) &&
1670 strcmp("local", cfg_obj_asstring(policy)) == 0)
1671 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1672
1673 /* Now check the grant policy */
1674 for (element = cfg_list_first(policy);
1675 element != NULL;
1676 element = cfg_list_next(element))
1677 {
1678 const cfg_obj_t *stmt = cfg_listelt_value(element);
1679 const cfg_obj_t *identity = cfg_tuple_get(stmt, "identity");
1680 const cfg_obj_t *matchtype = cfg_tuple_get(stmt, "matchtype");
1681 const cfg_obj_t *dname = cfg_tuple_get(stmt, "name");
1682 const cfg_obj_t *typelist = cfg_tuple_get(stmt, "types");
1683 dns_ssumatchtype_t mtype;
1684
1685 id = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixed_id);
1686 name = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixed_name);
1687
1688 tresult = dns_ssu_mtypefromstring(cfg_obj_asstring(matchtype),
1689 &mtype);
1690 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1691 cfg_obj_log(identity, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1692 "has a bad match-type");
1693 }
1694
1695 str = cfg_obj_asstring(identity);
1696 tresult = dns_name_fromstring(id, str, 1, NULL);
1697 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1698 cfg_obj_log(identity, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1699 "'%s' is not a valid name", str);
1700 result = tresult;
1701 }
1702
1703 /*
1704 * There is no name field for subzone and dname is void
1705 */
1706 if (mtype == dns_ssumatchtype_subdomain &&
1707 cfg_obj_isvoid(dname))
1708 {
1709 str = "."; /* Use "." as a replacement. */
1710 } else {
1711 str = cfg_obj_asstring(dname);
1712 }
1713 if (tresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1714 tresult = dns_name_fromstring(name, str, 0, NULL);
1715 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1716 cfg_obj_log(dname, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1717 "'%s' is not a valid name", str);
1718 result = tresult;
1719 }
1720 }
1721
1722 if (tresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS &&
1723 mtype == dns_ssumatchtype_wildcard &&
1724 !dns_name_iswildcard(name))
1725 {
1726 cfg_obj_log(identity, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1727 "'%s' is not a wildcard", str);
1728 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
1729 }
1730
1731 /*
1732 * For some match types, the name should be a placeholder
1733 * value, either "." or the same as identity.
1734 */
1735 switch (mtype) {
1736 case dns_ssumatchtype_self:
1737 case dns_ssumatchtype_selfsub:
1738 case dns_ssumatchtype_selfwild:
1739 if (tresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS &&
1740 (!dns_name_equal(id, name) &&
1741 !dns_name_equal(dns_rootname, name))) {
1742 cfg_obj_log(identity, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1743 "identity and name fields are not "
1744 "the same");
1745 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
1746 }
1747 break;
1748 case dns_ssumatchtype_selfkrb5:
1749 case dns_ssumatchtype_selfms:
1750 case dns_ssumatchtype_selfsubkrb5:
1751 case dns_ssumatchtype_selfsubms:
1752 case dns_ssumatchtype_tcpself:
1753 case dns_ssumatchtype_6to4self:
1754 if (tresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS &&
1755 !dns_name_equal(dns_rootname, name)) {
1756 cfg_obj_log(identity, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1757 "name field not set to "
1758 "placeholder value '.'");
1759 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
1760 }
1761 break;
1762 case dns_ssumatchtype_name:
1763 case dns_ssumatchtype_subdomain: /* also zonesub */
1764 case dns_ssumatchtype_subdomainms:
1765 case dns_ssumatchtype_subdomainkrb5:
1766 case dns_ssumatchtype_wildcard:
1767 case dns_ssumatchtype_external:
1768 case dns_ssumatchtype_local:
1769 if (tresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1770 DE_CONST(str, r.base);
1771 r.length = strlen(str);
1772 tresult = dns_rdatatype_fromtext(&type, &r);
1773 }
1774 if (tresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1775 cfg_obj_log(identity, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1776 "missing name field type '%s' "
1777 "found", str);
1778 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
1779 break;
1780 }
1781 break;
1782 default:
1783 INSIST(0);
1784 ISC_UNREACHABLE();
1785 }
1786
1787 for (element2 = cfg_list_first(typelist);
1788 element2 != NULL;
1789 element2 = cfg_list_next(element2))
1790 {
1791 const cfg_obj_t *typeobj;
1792
1793 typeobj = cfg_listelt_value(element2);
1794 DE_CONST(cfg_obj_asstring(typeobj), r.base);
1795 r.length = strlen(r.base);
1796
1797 tresult = dns_rdatatype_fromtext(&type, &r);
1798 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1799 cfg_obj_log(typeobj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1800 "'%s' is not a valid type", r.base);
1801 result = tresult;
1802 }
1803 }
1804 }
1805 return (result);
1806}

1813static isc_result_t

1836/*%
1837 * Check whether NOTIFY configuration at the zone level is acceptable for a
1838 * mirror zone. Return true if it is; return false otherwise.
1839 */
1840static bool
1841check_mirror_zone_notify(const cfg_obj_t *zoptions, const char *znamestr,
1842 isc_log_t *logctx)
1843{
1844 bool notify_configuration_ok = true;
1845 const cfg_obj_t *obj = NULL;
1846
1847 (void)cfg_map_get(zoptions, "notify", &obj);
1848 if (obj == NULL) {
1849 /*
1850 * "notify" not set at zone level. This is fine.
1851 */
1852 return (true);
1853 }
1854
1855 if (cfg_obj_isboolean(obj)) {
1856 if (cfg_obj_asboolean(obj)) {
1857 /*
1858 * "notify yes;" set at zone level. This is an error.
1859 */
1860 notify_configuration_ok = false;
1861 }
1862 } else {
1863 const char *notifystr = cfg_obj_asstring(obj);
1864 if (strcasecmp(notifystr, "explicit") != 0) {
1865 /*
1866 * Something else than "notify explicit;" set at zone
1867 * level. This is an error.
1868 */
1869 notify_configuration_ok = false;
1870 }
1871 }
1872
1873 if (!notify_configuration_ok) {
1874 cfg_obj_log(zoptions, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1875 "zone '%s': mirror zones can only be used with "
1876 "'notify no;' or 'notify explicit;'", znamestr);
1877 }
1878
1879 return (notify_configuration_ok);
1880}

1882/*%
1883 * Try to determine whether recursion is available in a view without resorting
1884 * to extraordinary measures: just check the "recursion" and "allow-recursion"
1885 * settings. The point is to prevent accidental mirror zone misuse rather than
1886 * to enforce some sort of policy. Recursion is assumed to be allowed by
1887 * default if it is not explicitly disabled.
1888 */
1889static bool
1890check_recursion(const cfg_obj_t *config, const cfg_obj_t *voptions,
1891 const cfg_obj_t *goptions, isc_log_t *logctx,
1892 cfg_aclconfctx_t *actx, isc_mem_t *mctx)
1893{
1894 dns_acl_t *acl = NULL;
1895 const cfg_obj_t *obj;
1896 isc_result_t result;
1897 bool retval = true;
1898
1899 /*
1900 * Check the "recursion" option first.
1901 */
1902 obj = NULL;
1903 result = ISC_R_NOTFOUND;
1904 if (voptions != NULL) {
1905 result = cfg_map_get(voptions, "recursion", &obj);
1906 }
1907 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS && goptions != NULL) {
1908 result = cfg_map_get(goptions, "recursion", &obj);
1909 }
1910 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS && !cfg_obj_asboolean(obj)) {
1911 retval = false;
1912 goto cleanup;
1913 }
1914
1915 /*
1916 * If recursion is not disabled by the "recursion" option, check
1917 * whether it is disabled by the "allow-recursion" ACL.
1918 */
1919 obj = NULL;
1920 result = ISC_R_NOTFOUND;
1921 if (voptions != NULL) {
1922 result = cfg_map_get(voptions, "allow-recursion", &obj);
1923 }
1924 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS && goptions != NULL) {
1925 result = cfg_map_get(goptions, "allow-recursion", &obj);
1926 }
1927 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1928 result = cfg_acl_fromconfig(obj, config, logctx, actx, mctx, 0,
1929 &acl);
1930 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1931 goto cleanup;
1932 }
1933 retval = !dns_acl_isnone(acl);
1934 }
1935
1936 cleanup:
1937 if (acl != NULL) {
1938 dns_acl_detach(&acl);
1939 }
1940
1941 return (retval);
1942}

1944static isc_result_t
1945check_zoneconf(const cfg_obj_t *zconfig, const cfg_obj_t *voptions,
1946 const cfg_obj_t *config, isc_symtab_t *symtab,
1947 isc_symtab_t *files, isc_symtab_t *inview,
1948 const char *viewname, dns_rdataclass_t defclass,
1949 cfg_aclconfctx_t *actx, isc_log_t *logctx, isc_mem_t *mctx)
1950{
1951 const char *znamestr;
1952 const char *typestr = NULL;
1953 const char *target = NULL;
1954 unsigned int ztype;
1955 const cfg_obj_t *zoptions, *goptions = NULL;
1956 const cfg_obj_t *obj = NULL;
1957 const cfg_obj_t *inviewobj = NULL;
1958 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
1959 isc_result_t tresult;
1960 unsigned int i;
1961 dns_rdataclass_t zclass;
1962 dns_fixedname_t fixedname;
1963 dns_name_t *zname = NULL; /* NULL if parsing of zone name fails. */
1964 isc_buffer_t b;
1965 bool root = false;

2070 /*
2071 * Look for an already existing zone.
2072 * We need to make this canonical as isc_symtab_define()
2073 * deals with strings.
2074 */
2075 dns_fixedname_init(&fixedname);
2076 isc_buffer_constinit(&b, znamestr, strlen(znamestr));
2077 isc_buffer_add(&b, strlen(znamestr));

2079 dns_rootname, DNS_NAME_DOWNCASE, NULL);
2080 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2081 cfg_obj_log(zconfig, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
2082 "zone '%s': is not a valid name", znamestr);
2083 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
2084 } else {

2086 char *tmp = namebuf;

2092 ztype == CFG_ZONE_HINT ? 1 :
2093 ztype == CFG_ZONE_REDIRECT ? 2 : 3,
2094 symtab, "zone '%s': already exists "
2095 "previous definition: %s:%u", logctx, mctx);

2099 root = true;
2100 else if (dns_name_isrfc1918(zname))
2101 rfc1918 = true;
2102 else if (dns_name_isula(zname))
2103 ula = true;
2104 tmp += strlen(tmp);
2105 len -= strlen(tmp);
2106 (void)snprintf(tmp, len, "%u/%s", zclass,
2107 (ztype == CFG_ZONE_INVIEW) ? target :
2108 (viewname != NULL) ? viewname : "_default");
2109 switch (ztype) {
2110 case CFG_ZONE_INVIEW:
2111 tresult = isc_symtab_lookup(inview, namebuf, 0, NULL);
2112 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2113 cfg_obj_log(inviewobj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
2114 "'in-view' zone '%s' "
2115 "does not exist in view '%s', "
2116 "or view '%s' is not yet defined",
2117 znamestr, target, target);
2118 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2119 result = tresult;
2120 }
2121 }
2122 break;
2123
2124 case CFG_ZONE_FORWARD:
2125 case CFG_ZONE_REDIRECT:
2126 case CFG_ZONE_DELEGATION:
2127 break;
2128
2129 case CFG_ZONE_MASTER:
2130 case CFG_ZONE_SLAVE:
2131 case CFG_ZONE_MIRROR:
2132 case CFG_ZONE_HINT:
2133 case CFG_ZONE_STUB:
2134 case CFG_ZONE_STATICSTUB:
2135 tmp = isc_mem_strdup(mctx, namebuf);
2136 if (tmp != NULL) {
2137 isc_symvalue_t symvalue;
2138
2139 symvalue.as_cpointer = NULL;
2140 tresult = isc_symtab_define(inview, tmp, 1,
2141 symvalue, isc_symexists_replace);
2142 if (tresult == ISC_R_NOMEMORY) {
2143 isc_mem_free(mctx, tmp);
2144 }
2145 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS &&
2146 tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2147 result = tresult;
2148 } else if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2149 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
2150 }
2151 break;
2152
2153 default:
2154 INSIST(0);
2155 ISC_UNREACHABLE();
2156 }
2157 }

2568 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
2569 }
2570 }
2571 }
2572
2573 /*
2574 * Check that max-zone-ttl isn't used with masterfile-format map
2575 */
2576 masterformat = dns_masterformat_text;
2577 obj = NULL;
2578 (void)cfg_map_get(zoptions, "masterfile-format", &obj);
2579 if (obj != NULL) {
2580 const char *masterformatstr = cfg_obj_asstring(obj);
2581 if (strcasecmp(masterformatstr, "text") == 0) {
2582 masterformat = dns_masterformat_text;
2583 } else if (strcasecmp(masterformatstr, "raw") == 0) {
2584 masterformat = dns_masterformat_raw;
2585 } else if (strcasecmp(masterformatstr, "map") == 0) {
2586 masterformat = dns_masterformat_map;
2587 } else {
2588 INSIST(0);
2589 ISC_UNREACHABLE();
2590 }
2591 }
2592
2593 if (masterformat == dns_masterformat_map) {
2594 obj = NULL;
2595 (void)cfg_map_get(zoptions, "max-zone-ttl", &obj);
2596 if (obj == NULL && voptions != NULL)
2597 (void)cfg_map_get(voptions, "max-zone-ttl", &obj);
2598 if (obj == NULL && goptions !=NULL)
2599 (void)cfg_map_get(goptions, "max-zone-ttl", &obj);
2600 if (obj != NULL) {
2601 cfg_obj_log(zconfig, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
2602 "zone '%s': 'max-zone-ttl' is not "
2603 "compatible with 'masterfile-format map'",
2604 znamestr);
2605 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
2606 }
2607 }
2608
2609 /*
2610 * Warn if key-directory doesn't exist
2611 */
2612 obj = NULL;
2613 tresult = cfg_map_get(zoptions, "key-directory", &obj);
2614 if (tresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2615 const char *dir = cfg_obj_asstring(obj);
2616 tresult = isc_file_isdirectory(dir);
2617 switch (tresult) {
2618 case ISC_R_SUCCESS:
2619 break;
2620 case ISC_R_FILENOTFOUND:
2621 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
2622 "key-directory: '%s' does not exist",
2623 dir);
2624 break;
2625 case ISC_R_INVALIDFILE:
2626 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
2627 "key-directory: '%s' is not a directory",
2628 dir);
2629 break;
2630 default:
2631 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
2632 "key-directory: '%s' %s",
2633 dir, isc_result_totext(tresult));
2634 result = tresult;
2635 }
2636 }
2637
2638 /*
2639 * Check various options.
2640 */
2641 tresult = check_options(zoptions, logctx, mctx, optlevel_zone);
2642 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2643 result = tresult;
2644
2645 /*
2646 * If the zone type is rbt/rbt64 then master/hint zones
2647 * require file clauses.
2648 * If inline signing is used, then slave zones require a
2649 * file clause as well
2650 */
2651 obj = NULL;
2652 dlz = false;
2653 tresult = cfg_map_get(zoptions, "dlz", &obj);
2654 if (tresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2655 dlz = true;
2656
2657 obj = NULL;
2658 tresult = cfg_map_get(zoptions, "database", &obj);
2659 if (dlz && tresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2660 cfg_obj_log(zconfig, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
2661 "zone '%s': cannot specify both 'dlz' "
2662 "and 'database'", znamestr);
2663 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
2664 } else if (!dlz &&
2665 (tresult == ISC_R_NOTFOUND ||
2666 (tresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS &&
2667 (strcmp("rbt", cfg_obj_asstring(obj)) == 0 ||
2668 strcmp("rbt64", cfg_obj_asstring(obj)) == 0))))
2669 {
2670 isc_result_t res1;
2671 const cfg_obj_t *fileobj = NULL;
2672 tresult = cfg_map_get(zoptions, "file", &fileobj);
2673 obj = NULL;
2674 res1 = cfg_map_get(zoptions, "inline-signing", &obj);
2675 if ((tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS &&
2676 (ztype == CFG_ZONE_MASTER || ztype == CFG_ZONE_HINT ||
2677 (ztype == CFG_ZONE_SLAVE && res1 == ISC_R_SUCCESS &&
2678 cfg_obj_asboolean(obj)))))
2679 {
2680 cfg_obj_log(zconfig, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
2681 "zone '%s': missing 'file' entry",
2682 znamestr);
2683 result = tresult;
2684 } else if (tresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS &&
2685 (ztype == CFG_ZONE_SLAVE ||
2686 ztype == CFG_ZONE_MIRROR || ddns))
2687 {
2688 tresult = fileexist(fileobj, files, true, logctx);
2689 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2690 result = tresult;
2691 } else if (tresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS &&
2692 (ztype == CFG_ZONE_MASTER ||
2693 ztype == CFG_ZONE_HINT))
2694 {
2695 tresult = fileexist(fileobj, files, false, logctx);
2696 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2697 result = tresult;
2698 }
2699 }
2700
2701 return (result);
2702}

2705typedef struct keyalgorithms {
2706 const char *name;
2707 uint16_t size;
2708} algorithmtable;
2709
2710isc_result_t
2711bind9_check_key(const cfg_obj_t *key, isc_log_t *logctx) {
2712 const cfg_obj_t *algobj = NULL;
2713 const cfg_obj_t *secretobj = NULL;
2714 const char *keyname = cfg_obj_asstring(cfg_map_getname(key));
2715 const char *algorithm;
2716 int i;
2717 size_t len = 0;
2718 isc_result_t result;
2719 isc_buffer_t buf;
2720 unsigned char secretbuf[1024];
2721 static const algorithmtable algorithms[] = {
2722 { "hmac-md5", 128 },
2723 { "hmac-md5.sig-alg.reg.int", 0 },
2724 { "hmac-md5.sig-alg.reg.int.", 0 },
2725 { "hmac-sha1", 160 },
2726 { "hmac-sha224", 224 },
2727 { "hmac-sha256", 256 },
2728 { "hmac-sha384", 384 },
2729 { "hmac-sha512", 512 },
2730 { NULL, 0 }
2731 };
2732
2733 (void)cfg_map_get(key, "algorithm", &algobj);
2734 (void)cfg_map_get(key, "secret", &secretobj);
2735 if (secretobj == NULL || algobj == NULL) {
2736 cfg_obj_log(key, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
2737 "key '%s' must have both 'secret' and "
2738 "'algorithm' defined",
2739 keyname);
2740 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
2741 }
2742
2743 isc_buffer_init(&buf, secretbuf, sizeof(secretbuf));
2744 result = isc_base64_decodestring(cfg_obj_asstring(secretobj), &buf);
2745 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2746 cfg_obj_log(secretobj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
2747 "bad secret '%s'", isc_result_totext(result));
2748 return (result);
2749 }
2750
2751 algorithm = cfg_obj_asstring(algobj);
2752 for (i = 0; algorithms[i].name != NULL; i++) {
2753 len = strlen(algorithms[i].name);
2754 if (strncasecmp(algorithms[i].name, algorithm, len) == 0 &&
2755 (algorithm[len] == '\0' ||
2756 (algorithms[i].size != 0 && algorithm[len] == '-')))
2757 break;
2758 }
2759 if (algorithms[i].name == NULL) {
2760 cfg_obj_log(algobj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
2761 "unknown algorithm '%s'", algorithm);
2762 return (ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
2763 }
2764 if (algorithm[len] == '-') {
2765 uint16_t digestbits;
2766 result = isc_parse_uint16(&digestbits, algorithm + len + 1, 10);
2767 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS || result == ISC_R_RANGE) {
2768 if (result == ISC_R_RANGE ||
2769 digestbits > algorithms[i].size) {
2770 cfg_obj_log(algobj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
2771 "key '%s' digest-bits too large "
2772 "[%u..%u]", keyname,
2773 algorithms[i].size / 2,
2774 algorithms[i].size);
2775 return (ISC_R_RANGE);
2776 }
2777 if ((digestbits % 8) != 0) {
2778 cfg_obj_log(algobj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
2779 "key '%s' digest-bits not multiple"
2780 " of 8", keyname);
2781 return (ISC_R_RANGE);
2782 }
2783 /*
2784 * Recommended minima for hmac algorithms.
2785 */
2786 if ((digestbits < (algorithms[i].size / 2U) ||
2787 (digestbits < 80U)))
2788 cfg_obj_log(algobj, logctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
2789 "key '%s' digest-bits too small "
2790 "[<%u]", keyname,
2791 algorithms[i].size/2);
2792 } else {
2793 cfg_obj_log(algobj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
2794 "key '%s': unable to parse digest-bits",
2795 keyname);
2796 return (result);
2797 }
2798 }
2799 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
2800}

2802static isc_result_t
2803fileexist(const cfg_obj_t *obj, isc_symtab_t *symtab, bool writeable,
2804 isc_log_t *logctx)
2805{
2806 isc_result_t result;
2807 isc_symvalue_t symvalue;
2808 unsigned int line;
2809 const char *file;
2810
2811 result = isc_symtab_lookup(symtab, cfg_obj_asstring(obj), 0, &symvalue);
2812 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2813 if (writeable) {
2814 file = cfg_obj_file(symvalue.as_cpointer);
2815 line = cfg_obj_line(symvalue.as_cpointer);
2816 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
2817 "writeable file '%s': already in use: "
2818 "%s:%u", cfg_obj_asstring(obj),
2819 file, line);
2820 return (ISC_R_EXISTS);
2821 }
2822 result = isc_symtab_lookup(symtab, cfg_obj_asstring(obj), 2,
2823 &symvalue);
2824 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2825 file = cfg_obj_file(symvalue.as_cpointer);
2826 line = cfg_obj_line(symvalue.as_cpointer);
2827 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
2828 "writeable file '%s': already in use: "
2829 "%s:%u", cfg_obj_asstring(obj),
2830 file, line);
2831 return (ISC_R_EXISTS);
2832 }
2833 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
2834 }
2835
2836 symvalue.as_cpointer = obj;
2837 result = isc_symtab_define(symtab, cfg_obj_asstring(obj),
2838 writeable ? 2 : 1, symvalue,
2839 isc_symexists_reject);
2840 return (result);
2841}

2843/*
2844 * Check key list for duplicates key names and that the key names
2845 * are valid domain names as these keys are used for TSIG.
2846 *
2847 * Check the key contents for validity.
2848 */
2849static isc_result_t
2850check_keylist(const cfg_obj_t *keys, isc_symtab_t *symtab,
2851 isc_mem_t *mctx, isc_log_t *logctx)
2852{
2853 char namebuf[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
2854 dns_fixedname_t fname;
2855 dns_name_t *name;
2856 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
2857 isc_result_t tresult;
2858 const cfg_listelt_t *element;
2859
2860 name = dns_fixedname_initname(&fname);
2861 for (element = cfg_list_first(keys);
2862 element != NULL;
2863 element = cfg_list_next(element))
2864 {
2865 const cfg_obj_t *key = cfg_listelt_value(element);
2866 const char *keyid = cfg_obj_asstring(cfg_map_getname(key));
2867 isc_symvalue_t symvalue;
2868 isc_buffer_t b;
2869 char *keyname;
2870
2871 isc_buffer_constinit(&b, keyid, strlen(keyid));
2872 isc_buffer_add(&b, strlen(keyid));
2873 tresult = dns_name_fromtext(name, &b, dns_rootname,
2874 0, NULL);
2875 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2876 cfg_obj_log(key, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
2877 "key '%s': bad key name", keyid);
2878 result = tresult;
2879 continue;
2880 }
2881 tresult = bind9_check_key(key, logctx);
2882 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2883 return (tresult);
2884
2885 dns_name_format(name, namebuf, sizeof(namebuf));
2886 keyname = isc_mem_strdup(mctx, namebuf);
2887 if (keyname == NULL)
2888 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
2889 symvalue.as_cpointer = key;
2890 tresult = isc_symtab_define(symtab, keyname, 1, symvalue,
2891 isc_symexists_reject);
2892 if (tresult == ISC_R_EXISTS) {
2893 const char *file;
2894 unsigned int line;
2895
2896 RUNTIME_CHECK(isc_symtab_lookup(symtab, keyname,
2897 1, &symvalue) == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
2898 file = cfg_obj_file(symvalue.as_cpointer);
2899 line = cfg_obj_line(symvalue.as_cpointer);
2900
2901 if (file == NULL)
2902 file = "<unknown file>";
2903 cfg_obj_log(key, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
2904 "key '%s': already exists "
2905 "previous definition: %s:%u",
2906 keyid, file, line);
2907 isc_mem_free(mctx, keyname);
2908 result = tresult;
2909 } else if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2910 isc_mem_free(mctx, keyname);
2911 return (tresult);
2912 }
2913 }
2914 return (result);
2915}

2953static isc_result_t
2954check_servers(const cfg_obj_t *config, const cfg_obj_t *voptions,
2955 isc_symtab_t *symtab, isc_log_t *logctx)
2956{
2957 dns_fixedname_t fname;
2958 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
2959 isc_result_t tresult;
2960 const cfg_listelt_t *e1, *e2;
2961 const cfg_obj_t *v1, *v2, *keys;
2962 const cfg_obj_t *servers;
2963 isc_netaddr_t n1, n2;
2964 unsigned int p1, p2;
2965 const cfg_obj_t *obj;
2966 char buf[ISC_NETADDR_FORMATSIZE];
2967 char namebuf[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
2968 const char *xfr;
2969 const char *keyval;
2970 isc_buffer_t b;
2971 int source;
2972 dns_name_t *keyname;
2973
2974 servers = NULL;
2975 if (voptions != NULL)
2976 (void)cfg_map_get(voptions, "server", &servers);
2977 if (servers == NULL)
2978 (void)cfg_map_get(config, "server", &servers);
2979 if (servers == NULL)
2980 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
2981
2982 for (e1 = cfg_list_first(servers); e1 != NULL; e1 = cfg_list_next(e1)) {
2983 v1 = cfg_listelt_value(e1);
2984 cfg_obj_asnetprefix(cfg_map_getname(v1), &n1, &p1);
2985 /*
2986 * Check that unused bits are zero.
2987 */
2988 tresult = isc_netaddr_prefixok(&n1, p1);
2989 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2990 INSIST(tresult == ISC_R_FAILURE);
2991 isc_netaddr_format(&n1, buf, sizeof(buf));
2992 cfg_obj_log(v1, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
2993 "server '%s/%u': invalid prefix "
2994 "(extra bits specified)", buf, p1);
2995 result = tresult;
2996 }
2997 source = 0;
2998 do {
2999 obj = NULL;
3000 if (n1.family == AF_INET)
3001 xfr = sources[source].v6;
3002 else
3003 xfr = sources[source].v4;
3004 (void)cfg_map_get(v1, xfr, &obj);
3005 if (obj != NULL) {
3006 isc_netaddr_format(&n1, buf, sizeof(buf));
3007 cfg_obj_log(v1, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
3008 "server '%s/%u': %s not legal",
3009 buf, p1, xfr);
3010 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
3011 }
3012 } while (sources[++source].v4 != NULL);
3013 e2 = e1;
3014 while ((e2 = cfg_list_next(e2)) != NULL) {
3015 v2 = cfg_listelt_value(e2);
3016 cfg_obj_asnetprefix(cfg_map_getname(v2), &n2, &p2);
3017 if (p1 == p2 && isc_netaddr_equal(&n1, &n2)) {
3018 const char *file = cfg_obj_file(v1);
3019 unsigned int line = cfg_obj_line(v1);
3020
3021 if (file == NULL)
3022 file = "<unknown file>";
3023
3024 isc_netaddr_format(&n2, buf, sizeof(buf));
3025 cfg_obj_log(v2, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
3026 "server '%s/%u': already exists "
3027 "previous definition: %s:%u",
3028 buf, p2, file, line);
3029 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
3030 }
3031 }
3032 keys = NULL;
3033 cfg_map_get(v1, "keys", &keys);
3034 if (keys != NULL) {
3035 /*
3036 * Normalize key name.
3037 */
3038 keyval = cfg_obj_asstring(keys);
3039 isc_buffer_constinit(&b, keyval, strlen(keyval));
3040 isc_buffer_add(&b, strlen(keyval));
3041 keyname = dns_fixedname_initname(&fname);
3042 tresult = dns_name_fromtext(keyname, &b, dns_rootname,
3043 0, NULL);
3044 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3045 cfg_obj_log(keys, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
3046 "bad key name '%s'", keyval);
3047 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
3048 continue;
3049 }
3050 dns_name_format(keyname, namebuf, sizeof(namebuf));
3051 tresult = isc_symtab_lookup(symtab, namebuf, 1, NULL);
3052 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3053 cfg_obj_log(keys, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
3054 "unknown key '%s'", keyval);
3055 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
3056 }
3057 }
3058 }
3059 return (result);
3060}

3062#define ROOT_KSK_2010 0x1
3063#define ROOT_KSK_2017 0x2
3064#define DLV_KSK_KEY 0x4
3065
3066static isc_result_t
3067check_trusted_key(const cfg_obj_t *key, bool managed,
3068 unsigned int *keyflags, isc_log_t *logctx)
3069{
3070 const char *keystr, *keynamestr;
3071 dns_fixedname_t fkeyname;
3072 dns_name_t *keyname;
3073 isc_buffer_t b;
3074 isc_region_t r;
3075 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
3076 isc_result_t tresult;
3077 uint32_t flags, proto, alg;
3078 unsigned char keydata[4096];
3079
3080 flags = cfg_obj_asuint32(cfg_tuple_get(key, "flags"));
3081 proto = cfg_obj_asuint32(cfg_tuple_get(key, "protocol"));
3082 alg = cfg_obj_asuint32(cfg_tuple_get(key, "algorithm"));
3083
3084 keyname = dns_fixedname_initname(&fkeyname);
3085 keynamestr = cfg_obj_asstring(cfg_tuple_get(key, "name"));
3086
3087 isc_buffer_constinit(&b, keynamestr, strlen(keynamestr));
3088 isc_buffer_add(&b, strlen(keynamestr));
3089 result = dns_name_fromtext(keyname, &b, dns_rootname, 0, NULL);
3090 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3091 cfg_obj_log(key, logctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING, "bad key name: %s\n",
3092 isc_result_totext(result));
3093 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
3094 }
3095
3096 if (flags > 0xffff) {
3097 cfg_obj_log(key, logctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
3098 "flags too big: %u\n", flags);
3099 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
3100 }
3101 if (proto > 0xff) {
3102 cfg_obj_log(key, logctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
3103 "protocol too big: %u\n", proto);
3104 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
3105 }
3106 if (alg > 0xff) {
3107 cfg_obj_log(key, logctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
3108 "algorithm too big: %u\n", alg);
3109 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
3110 }
3111
3112 if (managed) {
3113 const char *initmethod;
3114 initmethod = cfg_obj_asstring(cfg_tuple_get(key, "init"));
3115
3116 if (strcasecmp(initmethod, "initial-key") != 0) {
3117 cfg_obj_log(key, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
3118 "managed key '%s': "
3119 "invalid initialization method '%s'",
3120 keynamestr, initmethod);
3121 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
3122 }
3123 }
3124
3125 isc_buffer_init(&b, keydata, sizeof(keydata));
3126
3127 keystr = cfg_obj_asstring(cfg_tuple_get(key, "key"));
3128 tresult = isc_base64_decodestring(keystr, &b);
3129
3130 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3131 cfg_obj_log(key, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
3132 "%s", isc_result_totext(tresult));
3133 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
3134 } else {
3135 isc_buffer_usedregion(&b, &r);
3136
3137 if ((alg == DST_ALG_RSASHA1) &&
3138 r.length > 1 && r.base[0] == 1 && r.base[1] == 3)
3139 cfg_obj_log(key, logctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
3140 "%s key '%s' has a weak exponent",
3141 managed ? "managed" : "trusted",
3142 keynamestr);
3143 }
3144
3145 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS && dns_name_equal(keyname, dns_rootname)) {
3146 static const unsigned char root_ksk_2010[] = {
3147 0x03, 0x01, 0x00, 0x01, 0xa8, 0x00, 0x20, 0xa9,
3148 0x55, 0x66, 0xba, 0x42, 0xe8, 0x86, 0xbb, 0x80,
3149 0x4c, 0xda, 0x84, 0xe4, 0x7e, 0xf5, 0x6d, 0xbd,
3150 0x7a, 0xec, 0x61, 0x26, 0x15, 0x55, 0x2c, 0xec,
3151 0x90, 0x6d, 0x21, 0x16, 0xd0, 0xef, 0x20, 0x70,
3152 0x28, 0xc5, 0x15, 0x54, 0x14, 0x4d, 0xfe, 0xaf,
3153 0xe7, 0xc7, 0xcb, 0x8f, 0x00, 0x5d, 0xd1, 0x82,

3270typedef enum {
3271 special_zonetype_rpz,
3272 special_zonetype_catz
3273} special_zonetype_t;
3274
3275static isc_result_t
3276check_rpz_catz(const char *rpz_catz, const cfg_obj_t *rpz_obj,
3277 const char *viewname, isc_symtab_t *symtab, isc_log_t *logctx,
3278 special_zonetype_t specialzonetype)
3279{
3280 const cfg_listelt_t *element;
3281 const cfg_obj_t *obj, *nameobj, *zoneobj;
3282 const char *zonename, *zonetype;
3283 const char *forview = " for view ";
3284 isc_symvalue_t value;
3285 isc_result_t result, tresult;
3286 dns_fixedname_t fixed;
3287 dns_name_t *name;
3288 char namebuf[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
3289 unsigned int num_zones = 0;
3290
3291 if (viewname == NULL) {
3292 viewname = "";
3293 forview = "";
3294 }
3295 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
3296
3297 name = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixed);
3298 obj = cfg_tuple_get(rpz_obj, "zone list");
3299
3300 for (element = cfg_list_first(obj);
3301 element != NULL;
3302 element = cfg_list_next(element))
3303 {
3304 obj = cfg_listelt_value(element);
3305 nameobj = cfg_tuple_get(obj, "zone name");
3306 zonename = cfg_obj_asstring(nameobj);
3307 zonetype = "";
3308
3309 if (specialzonetype == special_zonetype_rpz) {
3310 if (++num_zones > 64) {
3311 cfg_obj_log(nameobj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
3312 "more than 64 response policy "
3313 "zones in view '%s'", viewname);
3314 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
3315 }
3316 }
3317
3318 tresult = dns_name_fromstring(name, zonename, 0, NULL);
3319 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3320 cfg_obj_log(nameobj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
3321 "bad domain name '%s'", zonename);
3322 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3323 result = tresult;
3324 continue;
3325 }
3326 dns_name_format(name, namebuf, sizeof(namebuf));
3327 tresult = isc_symtab_lookup(symtab, namebuf, 3, &value);
3328 if (tresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3329 obj = NULL;
3330 zoneobj = value.as_cpointer;
3331 if (zoneobj != NULL && cfg_obj_istuple(zoneobj))
3332 zoneobj = cfg_tuple_get(zoneobj, "options");
3333 if (zoneobj != NULL && cfg_obj_ismap(zoneobj))
3334 (void)cfg_map_get(zoneobj, "type", &obj);
3335 if (obj != NULL)
3336 zonetype = cfg_obj_asstring(obj);
3337 }
3338 if (strcasecmp(zonetype, "primary") != 0 &&
3339 strcasecmp(zonetype, "master") != 0 &&
3340 strcasecmp(zonetype, "secondary") != 0 &&
3341 strcasecmp(zonetype, "slave") != 0)
3342 {
3343 cfg_obj_log(nameobj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
3344 "%s '%s'%s%s is not a master or slave zone",
3345 rpz_catz, zonename, forview, viewname);
3346 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3347 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
3348 }
3349 }
3350 return (result);
3351}

3364/*%
3365 * A callback for the cfg_pluginlist_foreach() call in check_viewconf() below.
3366 * Since the point is to check configuration of all plugins even when
3367 * processing some of them fails, always return ISC_R_SUCCESS and indicate any
3368 * check failures through the 'check_result' variable passed in via the
3369 * 'callback_data' structure.
3370 */
3371static isc_result_t
3372check_one_plugin(const cfg_obj_t *config, const cfg_obj_t *obj,
3373 const char *plugin_path, const char *parameters,
3374 void *callback_data)
3375{
3376 struct check_one_plugin_data *data = callback_data;
3377 char full_path[PATH_MAX];
3378 isc_result_t result;
3379
3380 result = ns_plugin_expandpath(plugin_path,
3381 full_path, sizeof(full_path));
3382 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3383 cfg_obj_log(obj, data->lctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
3384 "%s: plugin check failed: "
3385 "unable to get full plugin path: %s",
3386 plugin_path, isc_result_totext(result));
3387 return (result);
3388 }
3389
3390 result = ns_plugin_check(full_path, parameters, config,
3391 cfg_obj_file(obj), cfg_obj_line(obj),
3392 data->mctx, data->lctx, data->actx);
3393 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3394 cfg_obj_log(obj, data->lctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
3395 "%s: plugin check failed: %s",
3396 full_path, isc_result_totext(result));
3397 *data->check_result = result;
3398 }
3399
3400 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
3401}

3405check_viewconf(const cfg_obj_t *config, const cfg_obj_t *voptions,
3406 const char *viewname, dns_rdataclass_t vclass,

3593 (void)cfg_map_get(options, "dnssec-validation", &obj);

3596 valstr = "yes";
3597 } else if (cfg_obj_isboolean(obj)) {
3598 enablevalidation = cfg_obj_asboolean(obj);
3599 valstr = enablevalidation ? "yes" : "no";
3600 } else {
3601 enablevalidation = true;
3602 valstr = "auto";
3603 }
3604

3608 valstr);

3611 * Check trusted-keys and managed-keys.
3612 */
3613 keys = NULL;
3614 if (voptions != NULL)
3615 (void)cfg_map_get(voptions, "trusted-keys", &keys);
3616 if (keys == NULL)
3617 (void)cfg_map_get(config, "trusted-keys", &keys);
3618
3619 tflags = 0;
3620 for (element = cfg_list_first(keys);
3621 element != NULL;
3622 element = cfg_list_next(element))
3623 {
3624 const cfg_obj_t *keylist = cfg_listelt_value(element);
3625 for (element2 = cfg_list_first(keylist);
3626 element2 != NULL;
3627 element2 = cfg_list_next(element2)) {
3628 obj = cfg_listelt_value(element2);
3629 tresult = check_trusted_key(obj, false, &tflags,
3630 logctx);
3631 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3632 result = tresult;
3633 }
3634 }
3635
3636 if ((tflags & ROOT_KSK_2010) != 0 && (tflags & ROOT_KSK_2017) == 0) {
3637 cfg_obj_log(keys, logctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
3638 "trusted-key for root from 2010 without updated "
3639 "trusted-key from 2017: THIS WILL FAIL AFTER "
3640 "KEY ROLLOVER");
3641 }
3642
3643 if ((tflags & DLV_KSK_KEY) != 0) {
3644 cfg_obj_log(keys, logctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
3645 "trusted-key for dlv.isc.org still present; "
3646 "dlv.isc.org has been shut down");
3647 }
3648
3649 keys = NULL;
3650 if (voptions != NULL)
3651 (void)cfg_map_get(voptions, "managed-keys", &keys);
3652 if (keys == NULL)
3653 (void)cfg_map_get(config, "managed-keys", &keys);
3654
3655 mflags = 0;
3656 for (element = cfg_list_first(keys);
3657 element != NULL;
3658 element = cfg_list_next(element))
3659 {
3660 const cfg_obj_t *keylist = cfg_listelt_value(element);
3661 for (element2 = cfg_list_first(keylist);
3662 element2 != NULL;
3663 element2 = cfg_list_next(element2)) {
3664 obj = cfg_listelt_value(element2);
3665 tresult = check_trusted_key(obj, true, &mflags,
3666 logctx);
3667 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3668 result = tresult;
3669 }
3670 }
3671
3672 if ((mflags & ROOT_KSK_2010) != 0 && (mflags & ROOT_KSK_2017) == 0) {
3673 cfg_obj_log(keys, logctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
3674 "managed-key for root from 2010 without updated "
3675 "managed-key from 2017");
3676 }
3677
3678 if ((mflags & DLV_KSK_KEY) != 0) {
3679 cfg_obj_log(keys, logctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
3680 "managed-key for dlv.isc.org still present; "
3681 "dlv.isc.org has been shut down");
3682 }
3683
3684 if ((tflags & (ROOT_KSK_2010|ROOT_KSK_2017)) != 0 &&
3685 (mflags & (ROOT_KSK_2010|ROOT_KSK_2017)) != 0)
3686 {
3687 cfg_obj_log(keys, logctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
3688 "both trusted-keys and managed-keys for the ICANN "
3689 "root are present");
3690 }
3691
3692 /*
3693 * Check options.
3694 */
3695 if (voptions != NULL)
3696 tresult = check_options(voptions, logctx, mctx,
3697 optlevel_view);
3698 else
3699 tresult = check_options(config, logctx, mctx,
3700 optlevel_config);
3701 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3702 result = tresult;
3703
3704 tresult = check_viewacls(actx, voptions, config, logctx, mctx);
3705 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3706 result = tresult;
3707
3708 tresult = check_recursionacls(actx, voptions, viewname,
3709 config, logctx, mctx);
3710 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3711 result = tresult;
3712
3713 tresult = check_dns64(actx, voptions, config, logctx, mctx);
3714 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3715 result = tresult;
3716
3717 tresult = check_ratelimit(actx, voptions, config, logctx, mctx);
3718 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3719 result = tresult;
3720
3721 /*
3722 * Load plugins.
3723 */
3724 if (check_plugins) {
3725 if (voptions != NULL) {
3726 (void)cfg_map_get(voptions, "plugin", &plugin_list);
3727 } else {
3728 (void)cfg_map_get(config, "plugin", &plugin_list);
3729 }
3730 }
3731
3732#ifdef HAVE_DLOPEN
3733 {
3734 struct check_one_plugin_data check_one_plugin_data = {
3735 .mctx = mctx,
3736 .lctx = logctx,
3737 .actx = actx,
3738 .check_result = &tresult,
3739 };
3740
3741 (void)cfg_pluginlist_foreach(config, plugin_list, logctx,
3742 check_one_plugin,
3743 &check_one_plugin_data);
3744 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3745 result = tresult;
3746 }
3747 }
3748#endif /* HAVE_DLOPEN */
3749
3750 cleanup:
3751 if (symtab != NULL)
3752 isc_symtab_destroy(&symtab);
3753 if (actx != NULL)
3754 cfg_aclconfctx_detach(&actx);
3755
3756 return (result);
3757}
