3759static const char *
3760default_channels[] = {
3761 "default_syslog",
3762 "default_stderr",
3763 "default_debug",
3764 "null",
3765 NULL
3766};
3767
3768static isc_result_t
3769bind9_check_logging(const cfg_obj_t *config, isc_log_t *logctx,
3770 isc_mem_t *mctx)
3771{
3772 const cfg_obj_t *categories = NULL;
3773 const cfg_obj_t *category;
3774 const cfg_obj_t *channels = NULL;
3775 const cfg_obj_t *channel;
3776 const cfg_listelt_t *element;
3777 const cfg_listelt_t *delement;
3778 const char *channelname;
3779 const char *catname;
3780 const cfg_obj_t *fileobj = NULL;
3781 const cfg_obj_t *syslogobj = NULL;
3782 const cfg_obj_t *nullobj = NULL;
3783 const cfg_obj_t *stderrobj = NULL;
3784 const cfg_obj_t *logobj = NULL;
3785 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
3786 isc_result_t tresult;
3787 isc_symtab_t *symtab = NULL;
3788 isc_symvalue_t symvalue;
3789 int i;
3790
3791 (void)cfg_map_get(config, "logging", &logobj);
3792 if (logobj == NULL)
3793 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
3794
3795 result = isc_symtab_create(mctx, 100, NULL, NULL, false, &symtab);
3796 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3797 return (result);
3798
3799 symvalue.as_cpointer = NULL;
3800 for (i = 0; default_channels[i] != NULL; i++) {
3801 tresult = isc_symtab_define(symtab, default_channels[i], 1,
3802 symvalue, isc_symexists_replace);
3803 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3804 result = tresult;
3805 }
3806
3807 cfg_map_get(logobj, "channel", &channels);
3808
3809 for (element = cfg_list_first(channels);
3810 element != NULL;
3811 element = cfg_list_next(element))
3812 {
3813 channel = cfg_listelt_value(element);
3814 channelname = cfg_obj_asstring(cfg_map_getname(channel));
3815 fileobj = syslogobj = nullobj = stderrobj = NULL;
3816 (void)cfg_map_get(channel, "file", &fileobj);
3817 (void)cfg_map_get(channel, "syslog", &syslogobj);
3818 (void)cfg_map_get(channel, "null", &nullobj);
3819 (void)cfg_map_get(channel, "stderr", &stderrobj);
3820 i = 0;
3821 if (fileobj != NULL)
3822 i++;
3823 if (syslogobj != NULL)
3824 i++;
3825 if (nullobj != NULL)
3826 i++;
3827 if (stderrobj != NULL)
3828 i++;
3829 if (i != 1) {
3830 cfg_obj_log(channel, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
3831 "channel '%s': exactly one of file, syslog, "
3832 "null, and stderr must be present",
3833 channelname);
3834 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
3835 }
3836 tresult = isc_symtab_define(symtab, channelname, 1,
3837 symvalue, isc_symexists_replace);
3838 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3839 result = tresult;
3840 }
3841
3842 cfg_map_get(logobj, "category", &categories);
3843
3844 for (element = cfg_list_first(categories);
3845 element != NULL;
3846 element = cfg_list_next(element))
3847 {
3848 category = cfg_listelt_value(element);
3849 catname = cfg_obj_asstring(cfg_tuple_get(category, "name"));
3850 if (isc_log_categorybyname(logctx, catname) == NULL) {
3851 cfg_obj_log(category, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
3852 "undefined category: '%s'", catname);
3853 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
3854 }
3855 channels = cfg_tuple_get(category, "destinations");
3856 for (delement = cfg_list_first(channels);
3857 delement != NULL;
3858 delement = cfg_list_next(delement))
3859 {
3860 channel = cfg_listelt_value(delement);
3861 channelname = cfg_obj_asstring(channel);
3862 tresult = isc_symtab_lookup(symtab, channelname, 1,
3863 &symvalue);
3864 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3865 cfg_obj_log(channel, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
3866 "undefined channel: '%s'",
3867 channelname);
3868 result = tresult;
3869 }
3870 }
3871 }
3872 isc_symtab_destroy(&symtab);
3873 return (result);
3874}

3876static isc_result_t
3877bind9_check_controlskeys(const cfg_obj_t *control, const cfg_obj_t *keylist,
3878 isc_log_t *logctx)
3879{
3880 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
3881 const cfg_obj_t *control_keylist;
3882 const cfg_listelt_t *element;
3883 const cfg_obj_t *key;
3884 const char *keyval;
3885
3886 control_keylist = cfg_tuple_get(control, "keys");
3887 if (cfg_obj_isvoid(control_keylist))
3888 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
3889
3890 for (element = cfg_list_first(control_keylist);
3891 element != NULL;
3892 element = cfg_list_next(element))
3893 {
3894 key = cfg_listelt_value(element);
3895 keyval = cfg_obj_asstring(key);
3896
3897 if (!rndckey_exists(keylist, keyval)) {
3898 cfg_obj_log(key, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
3899 "unknown key '%s'", keyval);
3900 result = ISC_R_NOTFOUND;
3901 }
3902 }
3903 return (result);
3904}
3905
3906static isc_result_t
3907bind9_check_controls(const cfg_obj_t *config, isc_log_t *logctx,
3908 isc_mem_t *mctx)
3909{
3910 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS, tresult;
3911 cfg_aclconfctx_t *actx = NULL;
3912 const cfg_listelt_t *element, *element2;
3913 const cfg_obj_t *allow;
3914 const cfg_obj_t *control;
3915 const cfg_obj_t *controls;
3916 const cfg_obj_t *controlslist = NULL;
3917 const cfg_obj_t *inetcontrols;
3918 const cfg_obj_t *unixcontrols;
3919 const cfg_obj_t *keylist = NULL;
3920 const char *path;
3921 uint32_t perm, mask;
3922 dns_acl_t *acl = NULL;
3923 isc_sockaddr_t addr;
3924 int i;
3925
3926 (void)cfg_map_get(config, "controls", &controlslist);
3927 if (controlslist == NULL)
3928 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
3929
3930 (void)cfg_map_get(config, "key", &keylist);
3931
3932 cfg_aclconfctx_create(mctx, &actx);
3933
3934 /*
3935 * INET: Check allow clause.
3936 * UNIX: Check "perm" for sanity, check path length.
3937 */
3938 for (element = cfg_list_first(controlslist);
3939 element != NULL;
3940 element = cfg_list_next(element)) {
3941 controls = cfg_listelt_value(element);
3942 unixcontrols = NULL;
3943 inetcontrols = NULL;
3944 (void)cfg_map_get(controls, "unix", &unixcontrols);
3945 (void)cfg_map_get(controls, "inet", &inetcontrols);
3946 for (element2 = cfg_list_first(inetcontrols);
3947 element2 != NULL;
3948 element2 = cfg_list_next(element2)) {
3949 control = cfg_listelt_value(element2);
3950 allow = cfg_tuple_get(control, "allow");
3951 tresult = cfg_acl_fromconfig(allow, config, logctx,
3952 actx, mctx, 0, &acl);
3953 if (acl != NULL)
3954 dns_acl_detach(&acl);
3955 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3956 result = tresult;
3957 tresult = bind9_check_controlskeys(control, keylist,
3958 logctx);
3959 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3960 result = tresult;
3961 }
3962 for (element2 = cfg_list_first(unixcontrols);
3963 element2 != NULL;
3964 element2 = cfg_list_next(element2)) {
3965 control = cfg_listelt_value(element2);
3966 path = cfg_obj_asstring(cfg_tuple_get(control, "path"));
3967 tresult = isc_sockaddr_frompath(&addr, path);
3968 if (tresult == ISC_R_NOSPACE) {
3969 cfg_obj_log(control, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
3970 "unix control '%s': path too long",
3971 path);
3972 result = ISC_R_NOSPACE;
3973 }
3974 perm = cfg_obj_asuint32(cfg_tuple_get(control, "perm"));
3975 for (i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
3976#ifdef NEED_SECURE_DIRECTORY
3977 mask = (0x1 << (i*3)); /* SEARCH */
3978#else
3979 mask = (0x6 << (i*3)); /* READ + WRITE */
3980#endif
3981 if ((perm & mask) == mask)
3982 break;
3983 }
3984 if (i == 0) {
3985 cfg_obj_log(control, logctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
3986 "unix control '%s' allows access "
3987 "to everyone", path);
3988 } else if (i == 3) {
3989 cfg_obj_log(control, logctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
3990 "unix control '%s' allows access "
3991 "to nobody", path);
3992 }
3993 tresult = bind9_check_controlskeys(control, keylist,
3994 logctx);
3995 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3996 result = tresult;
3997 }
3998 }
3999 cfg_aclconfctx_detach(&actx);
4000 return (result);
4001}

4003isc_result_t
4004bind9_check_namedconf(const cfg_obj_t *config, bool check_plugins,
4005 isc_log_t *logctx, isc_mem_t *mctx)
4006{
4007 const cfg_obj_t *options = NULL;
4008 const cfg_obj_t *views = NULL;
4009 const cfg_obj_t *acls = NULL;
4010 const cfg_obj_t *kals = NULL;
4011 const cfg_obj_t *obj;
4012 const cfg_listelt_t *velement;
4013 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
4014 isc_result_t tresult;
4015 isc_symtab_t *symtab = NULL;
4016 isc_symtab_t *files = NULL;
4017 isc_symtab_t *inview = NULL;
4018
4019 static const char *builtin[] = { "localhost", "localnets",
4020 "any", "none"};
4021
4022 (void)cfg_map_get(config, "options", &options);
4023
4024 if (options != NULL &&
4025 check_options(options, logctx, mctx,
4026 optlevel_options) != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
4027 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
4028
4029 if (bind9_check_logging(config, logctx, mctx) != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
4030 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
4031
4032 if (bind9_check_controls(config, logctx, mctx) != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
4033 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
4034
4035 (void)cfg_map_get(config, "view", &views);
4036
4037 if (views != NULL && options != NULL)
4038 if (check_dual_stack(options, logctx) != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
4039 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
4040
4041 /*
4042 * Use case insensitive comparision as not all file systems are
4043 * case sensitive. This will prevent people using FOO.DB and foo.db
4044 * on case sensitive file systems but that shouldn't be a major issue.
4045 */
4046 tresult = isc_symtab_create(mctx, 100, NULL, NULL, false,
4047 &files);
4048 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
4049 result = tresult;
4050 goto cleanup;
4051 }
4052
4053 tresult = isc_symtab_create(mctx, 100, freekey, mctx,

4056 result = tresult;
4057 goto cleanup;
4058 }
4059
4060 if (views == NULL) {
4061 tresult = check_viewconf(config, NULL, NULL,
4062 dns_rdataclass_in, files,
4063 check_plugins, inview, logctx, mctx);
4064 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS && tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
4065 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
4066 }
4067 } else {
4068 const cfg_obj_t *zones = NULL;
4069 const cfg_obj_t *plugins = NULL;
4070
4071 (void)cfg_map_get(config, "zone", &zones);
4072 if (zones != NULL) {
4073 cfg_obj_log(zones, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
4074 "when using 'view' statements, "
4075 "all zones must be in views");
4076 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
4077 }
4078
4079 (void)cfg_map_get(config, "plugin", &plugins);
4080 if (plugins != NULL) {
4081 cfg_obj_log(plugins, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
4082 "when using 'view' statements, "
4083 "all plugins must be defined in views");
4084 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
4085 }
4086 }
4087
4088 tresult = isc_symtab_create(mctx, 100, NULL, NULL, true, &symtab);
4089 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
4090 result = tresult;
4091 goto cleanup;
4092 }
4093 for (velement = cfg_list_first(views);
4094 velement != NULL;
4095 velement = cfg_list_next(velement))
4096 {
4097 const cfg_obj_t *view = cfg_listelt_value(velement);
4098 const cfg_obj_t *vname = cfg_tuple_get(view, "name");
4099 const cfg_obj_t *voptions = cfg_tuple_get(view, "options");
4100 const cfg_obj_t *vclassobj = cfg_tuple_get(view, "class");
4101 dns_rdataclass_t vclass = dns_rdataclass_in;
4102 const char *key = cfg_obj_asstring(vname);
4103 isc_symvalue_t symvalue;
4104 unsigned int symtype;
4105
4106 tresult = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
4107 if (cfg_obj_isstring(vclassobj)) {
4108 isc_textregion_t r;
4109
4110 DE_CONST(cfg_obj_asstring(vclassobj), r.base);
4111 r.length = strlen(r.base);
4112 tresult = dns_rdataclass_fromtext(&vclass, &r);
4113 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
4114 cfg_obj_log(vclassobj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
4115 "view '%s': invalid class %s",
4116 cfg_obj_asstring(vname), r.base);
4117 }
4118 symtype = vclass + 1;
4119 if (tresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS && symtab != NULL) {
4120 symvalue.as_cpointer = view;
4121 tresult = isc_symtab_define(symtab, key, symtype,
4122 symvalue,
4123 isc_symexists_reject);
4124 if (tresult == ISC_R_EXISTS) {
4125 const char *file;
4126 unsigned int line;
4127 RUNTIME_CHECK(isc_symtab_lookup(symtab, key,
4128 symtype, &symvalue) == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
4129 file = cfg_obj_file(symvalue.as_cpointer);
4130 line = cfg_obj_line(symvalue.as_cpointer);
4131 cfg_obj_log(view, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
4132 "view '%s': already exists "
4133 "previous definition: %s:%u",
4134 key, file, line);
4135 result = tresult;
4136 } else if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
4137 result = tresult;
4138 } else if ((strcasecmp(key, "_bind") == 0 &&
4139 vclass == dns_rdataclass_ch) ||
4140 (strcasecmp(key, "_default") == 0 &&
4141 vclass == dns_rdataclass_in)) {
4142 cfg_obj_log(view, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
4143 "attempt to redefine builtin view "
4144 "'%s'", key);
4145 result = ISC_R_EXISTS;
4146 }
4147 }
4148 if (tresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
4149 tresult = check_viewconf(config, voptions, key,
4150 vclass, files, check_plugins,
4151 inview, logctx, mctx);
4152 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
4153 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
4154 }
4155
4156 if (views != NULL && options != NULL) {
4157 obj = NULL;
4158 tresult = cfg_map_get(options, "cache-file", &obj);
4159 if (tresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
4160 cfg_obj_log(obj, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
4161 "'cache-file' cannot be a global "
4162 "option if views are present");
4163 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
4164 }
4165 }
4166
4167 cfg_map_get(config, "acl", &acls);
4168
4169 if (acls != NULL) {
4170 const cfg_listelt_t *elt;
4171 const cfg_listelt_t *elt2;
4172 const char *aclname;
4173
4174 for (elt = cfg_list_first(acls);
4175 elt != NULL;
4176 elt = cfg_list_next(elt)) {
4177 const cfg_obj_t *acl = cfg_listelt_value(elt);
4178 unsigned int line = cfg_obj_line(acl);
4179 unsigned int i;
4180
4181 aclname = cfg_obj_asstring(cfg_tuple_get(acl, "name"));
4182 for (i = 0;
4183 i < sizeof(builtin) / sizeof(builtin[0]);
4184 i++)
4185 if (strcasecmp(aclname, builtin[i]) == 0) {
4186 cfg_obj_log(acl, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
4187 "attempt to redefine "
4188 "builtin acl '%s'",
4189 aclname);
4190 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
4191 break;
4192 }
4193
4194 for (elt2 = cfg_list_next(elt);
4195 elt2 != NULL;
4196 elt2 = cfg_list_next(elt2)) {
4197 const cfg_obj_t *acl2 = cfg_listelt_value(elt2);
4198 const char *name;
4199 name = cfg_obj_asstring(cfg_tuple_get(acl2,
4200 "name"));
4201 if (strcasecmp(aclname, name) == 0) {
4202 const char *file = cfg_obj_file(acl);
4203
4204 if (file == NULL)
4205 file = "<unknown file>";
4206
4207 cfg_obj_log(acl2, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
4208 "attempt to redefine "
4209 "acl '%s' previous "
4210 "definition: %s:%u",
4211 name, file, line);
4212 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
4213 }
4214 }
4215 }
4216 }
4217
4218 tresult = cfg_map_get(config, "kal", &kals);
4219 if (tresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
4220 const cfg_listelt_t *elt;
4221 const cfg_listelt_t *elt2;
4222 const char *aclname;
4223
4224 for (elt = cfg_list_first(kals);
4225 elt != NULL;
4226 elt = cfg_list_next(elt)) {
4227 const cfg_obj_t *acl = cfg_listelt_value(elt);
4228
4229 aclname = cfg_obj_asstring(cfg_tuple_get(acl, "name"));
4230
4231 for (elt2 = cfg_list_next(elt);
4232 elt2 != NULL;
4233 elt2 = cfg_list_next(elt2)) {
4234 const cfg_obj_t *acl2 = cfg_listelt_value(elt2);
4235 const char *name;
4236 name = cfg_obj_asstring(cfg_tuple_get(acl2,
4237 "name"));
4238 if (strcasecmp(aclname, name) == 0) {
4239 const char *file = cfg_obj_file(acl);
4240 unsigned int line = cfg_obj_line(acl);
4241
4242 if (file == NULL)
4243 file = "<unknown file>";
4244
4245 cfg_obj_log(acl2, logctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
4246 "attempt to redefine "
4247 "kal '%s' previous "
4248 "definition: %s:%u",
4249 name, file, line);
4250 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
4251 }
4252 }
4253 }
4254 }
4255
4256cleanup:
4257 if (symtab != NULL)
4258 isc_symtab_destroy(&symtab);
4259 if (inview != NULL)
4260 isc_symtab_destroy(&inview);
4261 if (files != NULL)
4262 isc_symtab_destroy(&files);
4263
4264 return (result);
4265}
